const QUIZ_STUDY_ELECTRICIDAD=[{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un compresor trifásico de 208/230V consume 28A por fase. Si mides las tres fases y obtienes 28A, 32A y 27A, ¿cuál es el porcentaje de desbalance de corriente?","q_en":"A 208/230V three-phase compressor draws 28A per phase. If you measure 28A, 32A, and 27A on the three phases, what is the current imbalance percentage?","o":["8.5%","10.3%","12.1%","6.9%"],"o_en":["8.5%","10.3%","12.1%","6.9%"],"c":1,"e":"Promedio = (28+32+27)/3 = 29A. Mayor desviación = 32-29 = 3A. Desbalance = 3/29 × 100 = 10.3%.","e_en":"Average = (28+32+27)/3 = 29A. Greatest deviation = 32-29 = 3A. Imbalance = 3/29 × 100 = 10.3%.","a":"Promedio = (28+32+27)/3 = 29A. Mayor desviación = 32-29 = 3A. Desbalance = 3/29 × 100 = 10.3%.","a_en":"Average = (28+32+27)/3 = 29A. Greatest deviation = 32-29 = 3A. Imbalance = 3/29 × 100 = 10.3%."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un motor trifásico, un desbalance de voltaje del 3% puede causar un aumento de temperatura del devanado de aproximadamente:","q_en":"In a three-phase motor, a 3% voltage imbalance can cause a winding temperature increase of approximately:","o":["10%","25%","15%","35%"],"o_en":["10%","25%","15%","35%"],"c":1,"e":"La regla general es que el aumento de temperatura es aproximadamente el cuadrado del desbalance × factor. Un 3% de desbalance ≈ 25% más calor.","e_en":"General rule is temperature increase is approximately the square of imbalance × factor. 3% imbalance ≈ 25% more heat.","a":"La regla general es que el aumento de temperatura es aproximadamente el cuadrado del desbalance × factor. Un 3% de desbalance ≈ 25% más calor.","a_en":"General rule is temperature increase is approximately the square of imbalance × factor. 3% imbalance ≈ 25% more heat."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un VFD alimenta un motor de 10HP a 460V. Al reducir la frecuencia a 30Hz (de 60Hz), ¿qué voltaje aproximado debe entregar el VFD al motor?","q_en":"A VFD feeds a 10HP motor at 460V. When reducing frequency to 30Hz (from 60Hz), what approximate voltage should the VFD deliver to the motor?","o":["460V","230V","345V","115V"],"o_en":["460V","230V","345V","115V"],"c":1,"e":"Relación V/Hz constante: 460V/60Hz = 7.67 V/Hz. A 30Hz: 7.67 × 30 = 230V para mantener el torque.","e_en":"Constant V/Hz ratio: 460V/60Hz = 7.67 V/Hz. At 30Hz: 7.67 × 30 = 230V to maintain torque.","a":"Relación V/Hz constante: 460V/60Hz = 7.67 V/Hz. A 30Hz: 7.67 × 30 = 230V para mantener el torque.","a_en":"Constant V/Hz ratio: 460V/60Hz = 7.67 V/Hz. At 30Hz: 7.67 × 30 = 230V to maintain torque."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor trifásico de 460V, 15HP tiene FLA de 21A. ¿Cuál es el tamaño mínimo de breaker según NEC (250% del FLA para protección del circuito ramal)?","q_en":"A 460V, 15HP three-phase motor has 21A FLA. What is the minimum breaker size per NEC (250% of FLA for branch circuit protection)?","o":["40A","50A","60A","45A"],"o_en":["40A","50A","60A","45A"],"c":2,"e":"21A × 250% = 52.5A. Se redondea al próximo tamaño estándar superior = 60A.","e_en":"21A × 250% = 52.5A. Round up to next standard size = 60A.","a":"21A × 250% = 52.5A. Se redondea al próximo tamaño estándar superior = 60A.","a_en":"21A × 250% = 52.5A. Round up to next standard size = 60A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La potencia trifásica se calcula como P = √3 × V × I × PF. Si V=208V, I=30A y PF=0.85, ¿cuál es la potencia real?","q_en":"Three-phase power is calculated as P = √3 × V × I × PF. If V=208V, I=30A and PF=0.85, what is the real power?","o":["7,500 W","9,189 W","10,816 W","8,245 W"],"o_en":["7,500 W","9,189 W","10,816 W","8,245 W"],"c":1,"e":"P = 1.732 × 208 × 30 × 0.85 = 9,189W ≈ 9.2 kW.","e_en":"P = 1.732 × 208 × 30 × 0.85 = 9,189W ≈ 9.2 kW.","a":"P = 1.732 × 208 × 30 × 0.85 = 9,189W ≈ 9.2 kW.","a_en":"P = 1.732 × 208 × 30 × 0.85 = 9,189W ≈ 9.2 kW."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un transformador de control de 75VA alimenta un circuito de 24V. ¿Cuál es el amperaje máximo que puede entregar el secundario?","q_en":"A 75VA control transformer powers a 24V circuit. What is the maximum amperage the secondary can deliver?","o":["2.5A","3.125A","3.75A","4.0A"],"o_en":["2.5A","3.125A","3.75A","4.0A"],"c":1,"e":"I = VA ÷ V = 75 ÷ 24 = 3.125A máximo.","e_en":"I = VA ÷ V = 75 ÷ 24 = 3.125A maximum.","a":"I = VA ÷ V = 75 ÷ 24 = 3.125A máximo.","a_en":"I = VA ÷ V = 75 ÷ 24 = 3.125A maximum."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un circuito de control de 24V tiene: un contactor (20VA), una válvula solenoide (8VA) y un relé (5VA). ¿Qué tamaño mínimo de transformador necesitas?","q_en":"A 24V control circuit has: a contactor (20VA), a solenoid valve (8VA) and a relay (5VA). What minimum transformer size do you need?","o":["25 VA","40 VA","50 VA","30 VA"],"o_en":["25 VA","40 VA","50 VA","30 VA"],"c":1,"e":"Carga total = 20+8+5 = 33VA. Agrega 20% de margen de seguridad = 39.6VA. El próximo tamaño estándar es 40VA.","e_en":"Total load = 20+8+5 = 33VA. Add 20% safety margin = 39.6VA. Next standard size is 40VA.","a":"Carga total = 20+8+5 = 33VA. Agrega 20% de margen de seguridad = 39.6VA. El próximo tamaño estándar es 40VA.","a_en":"Total load = 20+8+5 = 33VA. Add 20% safety margin = 39.6VA. Next standard size is 40VA."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un compresor de 5 toneladas a 208/230V tiene datos de placa: RLA 24A, LRA 138A. El MCA (Minimum Circuit Ampacity) es:","q_en":"A 5-ton compressor at 208/230V has nameplate data: RLA 24A, LRA 138A. The MCA (Minimum Circuit Ampacity) is:","o":["24A","30A","34.8A","28A"],"o_en":["24A","30A","34.8A","28A"],"c":1,"e":"MCA típicamente se indica en la placa del equipo. Si se calcula: MCA = 1.25 × RLA = 1.25 × 24 = 30A.","e_en":"MCA is typically listed on equipment nameplate. If calculated: MCA = 1.25 × RLA = 1.25 × 24 = 30A.","a":"MCA típicamente se indica en la placa del equipo. Si se calcula: MCA = 1.25 × RLA = 1.25 × 24 = 30A.","a_en":"MCA is typically listed on equipment nameplate. If calculated: MCA = 1.25 × RLA = 1.25 × 24 = 30A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un circuito con un motor de compresor y un motor de ventilador, el MCA del equipo se calcula como:","q_en":"In a circuit with a compressor motor and a fan motor, the equipment MCA is calculated as:","o":["Suma de ambos FLA","1.25 × FLA del motor más grande + FLA de los demás motores","1.25 × suma de todos los FLA","FLA del motor más grande × 2"],"o_en":["Sum of both FLA","1.25 × FLA of largest motor + FLA of other motors","1.25 × sum of all FLA","FLA of largest motor × 2"],"c":1,"e":"MCA = (1.25 × FLA del motor más grande) + FLA de los demás motores y cargas. Esto asegura cable adecuado para el arranque.","e_en":"MCA = (1.25 × FLA of largest motor) + FLA of other motors and loads. This ensures adequate wire for starting.","a":"MCA = (1.25 × FLA del motor más grande) + FLA de los demás motores y cargas. Esto asegura cable adecuado para el arranque.","a_en":"MCA = (1.25 × FLA of largest motor) + FLA of other motors and loads. This ensures adequate wire for starting."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un condensador tiene: compresor RLA 24A, motor ventilador FLA 2.8A. El MCA es:","q_en":"A condensing unit has: compressor RLA 24A, fan motor FLA 2.8A. The MCA is:","o":["26.8A","32.8A","30A","35.6A"],"o_en":["26.8A","32.8A","30A","35.6A"],"c":1,"e":"MCA = (1.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 30 + 2.8 = 32.8A.","e_en":"MCA = (1.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 30 + 2.8 = 32.8A.","a":"MCA = (1.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 30 + 2.8 = 32.8A.","a_en":"MCA = (1.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 30 + 2.8 = 32.8A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"El MOCP (Maximum Overcurrent Protection) para el mismo condensador (RLA 24A, motor ventilador 2.8A) usando breaker es:","q_en":"The MOCP (Maximum Overcurrent Protection) for the same condensing unit (RLA 24A, fan motor 2.8A) using a breaker is:","o":["35A","45A","50A","40A"],"o_en":["35A","45A","50A","40A"],"c":1,"e":"MOCP típicamente se indica en la placa. Si se calcula: (2.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 56.8A. El fabricante indica 45A como MOCP.","e_en":"MOCP is typically listed on nameplate. If calculated: (2.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 56.8A. Manufacturer indicates 45A as MOCP.","a":"MOCP típicamente se indica en la placa. Si se calcula: (2.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 56.8A. El fabricante indica 45A como MOCP.","a_en":"MOCP is typically listed on nameplate. If calculated: (2.25 × 24) + 2.8 = 56.8A. Manufacturer indicates 45A as MOCP."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un termistor PTC colocado en el devanado de un motor sirve como protección contra:","q_en":"A PTC thermistor placed on a motor winding serves as protection against:","o":["Bajo voltaje","Sobrecalentamiento del devanado","Sobrecorriente instantánea","Falla de fase"],"o_en":["Low voltage","Winding overheating","Instantaneous overcurrent","Phase failure"],"c":1,"e":"El PTC embebido en el devanado aumenta su resistencia con la temperatura. Al sobrecalentarse, la alta resistencia activa la protección.","e_en":"The PTC embedded in the winding increases resistance with temperature. When overheating, high resistance triggers protection.","a":"El PTC embebido en el devanado aumenta su resistencia con la temperatura. Al sobrecalentarse, la alta resistencia activa la protección.","a_en":"The PTC embedded in the winding increases resistance with temperature. When overheating, high resistance triggers protection."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor con protección interna (internal overload) se dispara y no resetea inmediatamente. Debes:","q_en":"A motor with internal protection (internal overload) trips and won't immediately reset. You should:","o":["Puentear la protección para probar","Esperar a que se enfríe (puede tomar 30-60 minutos) y diagnosticar la causa del sobrecalentamiento","Reemplazar el motor inmediatamente","Aplicar hielo sobre el compresor"],"o_en":["Bypass the protection to test","Wait for it to cool down (can take 30-60 minutes) and diagnose the overheating cause","Replace the motor immediately","Apply ice on the compressor"],"c":1,"e":"Las protecciones internas son de auto-reseteo. Espera que se enfríe y luego diagnostica la causa del sobrecalentamiento antes de reiniciar.","e_en":"Internal protections are auto-reset. Wait for cool-down, then diagnose the overheating cause before restarting.","a":"Las protecciones internas son de auto-reseteo. Espera que se enfríe y luego diagnostica la causa del sobrecalentamiento antes de reiniciar.","a_en":"Internal protections are auto-reset. Wait for cool-down, then diagnose the overheating cause before restarting."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un diagrama de ladder (escalera), los componentes de carga se dibujan:","q_en":"In a ladder diagram, load components are drawn:","o":["En el lado izquierdo, junto a L1","Entre los dos rieles de alimentación (L1 y L2/N)","Solo en el lado derecho, junto a L2","Fuera de los rieles de alimentación"],"o_en":["On the left side, next to L1","Between the two power rails (L1 and L2/N)","Only on the right side, next to L2","Outside the power rails"],"c":1,"e":"En un diagrama de escalera, las cargas (bobinas, motores, luces) se conectan entre L1 y L2, con controles en serie antes de la carga.","e_en":"In a ladder diagram, loads (coils, motors, lights) connect between L1 and L2, with controls in series before the load.","a":"En un diagrama de escalera, las cargas (bobinas, motores, luces) se conectan entre L1 y L2, con controles en serie antes de la carga.","a_en":"In a ladder diagram, loads (coils, motors, lights) connect between L1 and L2, with controls in series before the load."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un diagrama de escalera, dos contactos en serie representan una función lógica:","q_en":"In a ladder diagram, two contacts in series represent a logic function of:","o":["OR (O)","AND (Y)","NOT (NO)","XOR"],"o_en":["OR","AND","NOT","XOR"],"c":1,"e":"Contactos en serie = AND. Ambos deben estar cerrados para que la corriente fluya. En paralelo = OR (cualquiera permite el flujo).","e_en":"Contacts in series = AND. Both must be closed for current to flow. In parallel = OR (either allows flow).","a":"Contactos en serie = AND. Ambos deben estar cerrados para que la corriente fluya. En paralelo = OR (cualquiera permite el flujo).","a_en":"Contacts in series = AND. Both must be closed for current to flow. In parallel = OR (either allows flow)."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un relay con designación '2PDT' tiene:","q_en":"A relay with designation '2PDT' has:","o":["2 polos, simple tiro","2 polos, doble tiro (cada polo tiene NO y NC)","1 polo, doble tiro","2 polos sin posición central"],"o_en":["2 poles, single throw","2 poles, double throw (each pole has NO and NC)","1 pole, double throw","2 poles with no center position"],"c":1,"e":"2PDT = 2 Poles Double Throw. Tiene 2 conjuntos de contactos independientes, cada uno con posición NO y NC.","e_en":"2PDT = 2 Poles Double Throw. Has 2 independent contact sets, each with NO and NC positions.","a":"2PDT = 2 Poles Double Throw. Tiene 2 conjuntos de contactos independientes, cada uno con posición NO y NC.","a_en":"2PDT = 2 Poles Double Throw. Has 2 independent contact sets, each with NO and NC positions."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un contactor de compresor de 40A tiene una resistencia de contacto que ha aumentado a 0.5Ω por desgaste. ¿Cuánta potencia se disipa en los contactos con 30A de carga?","q_en":"A 40A compressor contactor has contact resistance that increased to 0.5Ω from wear. How much power is dissipated in the contacts at 30A load?","o":["300W","450W","150W","600W"],"o_en":["300W","450W","150W","600W"],"c":1,"e":"P = I² × R = 30² × 0.5 = 900 × 0.5 = 450W disipados en calor en los contactos. Esto es excesivo y peligroso.","e_en":"P = I² × R = 30² × 0.5 = 900 × 0.5 = 450W dissipated as heat in contacts. This is excessive and dangerous.","a":"P = I² × R = 30² × 0.5 = 900 × 0.5 = 450W disipados en calor en los contactos. Esto es excesivo y peligroso.","a_en":"P = I² × R = 30² × 0.5 = 900 × 0.5 = 450W dissipated as heat in contacts. This is excessive and dangerous."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al medir un circuito de 24V con un multímetro y obtienes 24V pero el componente no funciona, ¿qué está pasando (phantom voltage)?","q_en":"When measuring a 24V circuit with a multimeter and you get 24V but the component doesn't work, what's happening (phantom voltage)?","o":["El multímetro está defectuoso","El multímetro de alta impedancia lee voltaje inducido/fantasma; no hay corriente real disponible","El voltaje es correcto pero la frecuencia es incorrecta","El componente necesita más de 24V"],"o_en":["The multimeter is defective","High-impedance multimeter reads induced/phantom voltage; no real current available","Voltage is correct but frequency is wrong","Component needs more than 24V"],"c":1,"e":"Los multímetros digitales de alta impedancia pueden leer voltaje fantasma (inducido por cables cercanos). Usa función LoZ o un wiggy para confirmar.","e_en":"High-impedance digital multimeters can read phantom voltage (induced by nearby wires). Use LoZ function or a wiggy to confirm.","a":"Los multímetros digitales de alta impedancia pueden leer voltaje fantasma (inducido por cables cercanos). Usa función LoZ o un wiggy para confirmar.","a_en":"High-impedance digital multimeters can read phantom voltage (induced by nearby wires). Use LoZ function or a wiggy to confirm."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Para medir la corriente de fuga a tierra en un compresor, colocas la pinza amperimétrica alrededor de TODOS los conductores de alimentación juntos. Si lees 0.5A, indica:","q_en":"To measure ground leakage current on a compressor, you place the clamp meter around ALL power conductors together. If you read 0.5A, it indicates:","o":["Operación normal","Corriente de fuga a tierra de 0.5A (posible aislamiento deteriorado)","Lectura incorrecta, debería ser 0A siempre","El amperímetro necesita calibración"],"o_en":["Normal operation","0.5A ground leakage current (possible deteriorated insulation)","Incorrect reading, should always be 0A","Ammeter needs calibration"],"c":1,"e":"Con todos los conductores juntos, las corrientes deben cancelarse (lectura 0). Cualquier lectura indica fuga a tierra. 0.5A es significativo.","e_en":"With all conductors together, currents should cancel (0 reading). Any reading indicates ground leakage. 0.5A is significant.","a":"Con todos los conductores juntos, las corrientes deben cancelarse (lectura 0). Cualquier lectura indica fuga a tierra. 0.5A es significativo.","a_en":"With all conductors together, currents should cancel (0 reading). Any reading indicates ground leakage. 0.5A is significant."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor de compresor mide: C-R = 1.5Ω, C-S = 4.2Ω, R-S = 4.8Ω. ¿Qué indica?","q_en":"A compressor motor measures: C-R = 1.5Ω, C-S = 4.2Ω, R-S = 4.8Ω. What does it indicate?","o":["Devanados en buenas condiciones","Posible cortocircuito parcial en un devanado (los valores no cuadran)","Motor a tierra","Devanado de arranque abierto"],"o_en":["Windings in good condition","Possible partial short in a winding (values don't add up)","Grounded motor","Start winding open"],"c":1,"e":"C-R + C-S = 1.5 + 4.2 = 5.7Ω, pero R-S = 4.8Ω. Debería ser 5.7Ω. La diferencia indica cortocircuito parcial entre espiras.","e_en":"C-R + C-S = 1.5 + 4.2 = 5.7Ω, but R-S = 4.8Ω. Should be 5.7Ω. The difference indicates partial short between turns.","a":"C-R + C-S = 1.5 + 4.2 = 5.7Ω, pero R-S = 4.8Ω. Debería ser 5.7Ω. La diferencia indica cortocircuito parcial entre espiras.","a_en":"C-R + C-S = 1.5 + 4.2 = 5.7Ω, but R-S = 4.8Ω. Should be 5.7Ω. The difference indicates partial short between turns."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor ECM X13 tiene un módulo de control que recibe señal del air handler board. Si el módulo falla, ¿qué puedes hacer en emergencia?","q_en":"An X13 ECM motor has a control module receiving signal from the air handler board. If the module fails, what can you do in an emergency?","o":["Conectar directamente a 120V sin módulo","Reemplazar solo el módulo, el motor puede conservarse","Convertir a motor PSC sin cambios","No hay solución temporal, reemplazar motor completo"],"o_en":["Connect directly to 120V without module","Replace only the module, motor can be kept","Convert to PSC motor without changes","No temporary solution, replace entire motor"],"c":1,"e":"En los motores X13/ECM, el módulo de control es reemplazable separadamente. El motor magnético puede conservarse si está en buen estado.","e_en":"On X13/ECM motors, the control module is separately replaceable. The magnetic motor can be kept if in good condition.","a":"En los motores X13/ECM, el módulo de control es reemplazable separadamente. El motor magnético puede conservarse si está en buen estado.","a_en":"On X13/ECM motors, the control module is separately replaceable. The magnetic motor can be kept if in good condition."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La diferencia principal entre un motor ECM variable speed y un X13 es que:","q_en":"The main difference between a variable speed ECM motor and an X13 is that:","o":["El X13 es más eficiente","El variable speed mantiene CFM constante ajustando RPM; el X13 tiene velocidades preseleccionadas como un PSC","No hay diferencia significativa","El X13 es más caro"],"o_en":["X13 is more efficient","Variable speed maintains constant CFM by adjusting RPM; X13 has preset speeds like a PSC","No significant difference","X13 is more expensive"],"c":1,"e":"ECM variable speed ajusta RPM para mantener CFM constante bajo cualquier presión estática. X13 tiene velocidades preseleccionadas como PSC pero con más eficiencia.","e_en":"Variable speed ECM adjusts RPM to maintain constant CFM under any static pressure. X13 has preset speeds like PSC but with more efficiency.","a":"ECM variable speed ajusta RPM para mantener CFM constante bajo cualquier presión estática. X13 tiene velocidades preseleccionadas como PSC pero con más eficiencia.","a_en":"Variable speed ECM adjusts RPM to maintain constant CFM under any static pressure. X13 has preset speeds like PSC but with more efficiency."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al diagnosticar un inverter mini-split, el board muestra código de error E6. Después de buscar, indica problema de comunicación. El primer paso es:","q_en":"When diagnosing an inverter mini-split, the board shows error code E6. After research, it indicates communication problem. The first step is:","o":["Reemplazar el board de control","Verificar el cableado de comunicación entre unidad interior y exterior (voltaje, continuidad, conexiones)","Reemplazar el compresor inverter","Reiniciar el sistema desde el breaker"],"o_en":["Replace control board","Check communication wiring between indoor and outdoor units (voltage, continuity, connections)","Replace inverter compressor","Reset system from breaker"],"c":1,"e":"Error de comunicación: primero verifica el cableado de señal entre unidades. Revisa voltaje, conexiones flojas, y continuidad del cable de comunicación.","e_en":"Communication error: first check signal wiring between units. Check voltage, loose connections, and communication wire continuity.","a":"Error de comunicación: primero verifica el cableado de señal entre unidades. Revisa voltaje, conexiones flojas, y continuidad del cable de comunicación.","a_en":"Communication error: first check signal wiring between units. Check voltage, loose connections, and communication wire continuity."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema mini-split inverter mide 305VDC en el bus DC del board. El voltaje de alimentación es 230VAC. ¿Es esto normal?","q_en":"An inverter mini-split system measures 305VDC on the board's DC bus. Supply voltage is 230VAC. Is this normal?","o":["No, debería ser 230VDC","Sí, el voltaje DC rectificado es V × √2 ≈ 325VDC (305 es aceptable)","No, indica un capacitor del bus defectuoso","Sí, pero solo durante el arranque"],"o_en":["No, should be 230VDC","Yes, rectified DC voltage is V × √2 ≈ 325VDC (305 is acceptable)","No, indicates defective bus capacitor","Yes, but only during startup"],"c":1,"e":"230VAC × 1.414 (√2) = 325VDC es el pico teórico. En la práctica, 290-340VDC es normal bajo carga.","e_en":"230VAC × 1.414 (√2) = 325VDC is theoretical peak. In practice, 290-340VDC is normal under load.","a":"230VAC × 1.414 (√2) = 325VDC es el pico teórico. En la práctica, 290-340VDC es normal bajo carga.","a_en":"230VAC × 1.414 (√2) = 325VDC is theoretical peak. In practice, 290-340VDC is normal under load."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un IPM (Intelligent Power Module) en un inverter mini-split falla repetidamente. ¿Cuál es la causa más probable?","q_en":"An IPM (Intelligent Power Module) in an inverter mini-split keeps failing. What is the most probable cause?","o":["Board de control defectuoso","Compresor con devanado en corto o a tierra que daña el IPM por sobrecorriente","Voltaje de alimentación demasiado bajo","Filtro de aire sucio"],"o_en":["Defective control board","Compressor with shorted or grounded winding damaging IPM from overcurrent","Supply voltage too low","Dirty air filter"],"c":1,"e":"Un IPM que falla repetidamente generalmente indica compresor con problema eléctrico (corto parcial o tierra) que causa sobrecorriente y destruye el módulo.","e_en":"An IPM that fails repeatedly usually indicates a compressor with electrical problem (partial short or ground) causing overcurrent that destroys the module.","a":"Un IPM que falla repetidamente generalmente indica compresor con problema eléctrico (corto parcial o tierra) que causa sobrecorriente y destruye el módulo.","a_en":"An IPM that fails repeatedly usually indicates a compressor with electrical problem (partial short or ground) causing overcurrent that destroys the module."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Para medir la resistencia de aislamiento de un compresor con megóhmetro, ¿qué voltaje de prueba usas para un compresor de 230V?","q_en":"To measure insulation resistance of a compressor with a megohmmeter, what test voltage do you use for a 230V compressor?","o":["250 VDC","500 VDC","1000 VDC","100 VDC"],"o_en":["250 VDC","500 VDC","1000 VDC","100 VDC"],"c":1,"e":"Para motores de 230V, se usa 500VDC de prueba. La regla general es: voltaje de prueba = 2× voltaje nominal + 1000 (para motores grandes), o 500V para la mayoría de HVAC.","e_en":"For 230V motors, use 500VDC test voltage. General rule: test voltage = 2× rated voltage + 1000 (for large motors), or 500V for most HVAC.","a":"Para motores de 230V, se usa 500VDC de prueba. La regla general es: voltaje de prueba = 2× voltaje nominal + 1000 (para motores grandes), o 500V para la mayoría de HVAC.","a_en":"For 230V motors, use 500VDC test voltage. General rule: test voltage = 2× rated voltage + 1000 (for large motors), or 500V for most HVAC."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La regla del '1 megaohmio por 1000V' para aislamiento de motor significa que un motor de 460V necesita mínimo:","q_en":"The '1 megohm per 1000V' insulation rule means a 460V motor needs a minimum of:","o":["0.46 MΩ","1 MΩ (mínimo absoluto)","4.6 MΩ","2 MΩ"],"o_en":["0.46 MΩ","1 MΩ (absolute minimum)","4.6 MΩ","2 MΩ"],"c":1,"e":"La regla dice 1MΩ/1000V, pero el mínimo absoluto aceptado nunca debe ser menor a 1MΩ independientemente del voltaje.","e_en":"The rule says 1MΩ/1000V, but the absolute minimum accepted should never be less than 1MΩ regardless of voltage.","a":"La regla dice 1MΩ/1000V, pero el mínimo absoluto aceptado nunca debe ser menor a 1MΩ independientemente del voltaje.","a_en":"The rule says 1MΩ/1000V, but the absolute minimum accepted should never be less than 1MΩ regardless of voltage."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un arrancador suave (soft starter) para un motor reduce durante el arranque:","q_en":"A soft starter for a motor reduces during startup:","o":["Solo la frecuencia","El voltaje aplicado al motor gradualmente, reduciendo corriente de arranque y estrés mecánico","La resistencia del devanado","La impedancia del circuito"],"o_en":["Only frequency","Voltage applied to motor gradually, reducing starting current and mechanical stress","Winding resistance","Circuit impedance"],"c":1,"e":"El soft starter incrementa gradualmente el voltaje al motor usando SCRs/tiristores, reduciendo el pico de corriente de arranque y el estrés mecánico.","e_en":"The soft starter gradually increases voltage to the motor using SCRs/thyristors, reducing starting current spike and mechanical stress.","a":"El soft starter incrementa gradualmente el voltaje al motor usando SCRs/tiristores, reduciendo el pico de corriente de arranque y el estrés mecánico.","a_en":"The soft starter gradually increases voltage to the motor using SCRs/thyristors, reducing starting current spike and mechanical stress."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La diferencia entre un soft starter y un VFD es que:","q_en":"The difference between a soft starter and a VFD is that:","o":["Son exactamente iguales","El soft starter solo controla arranque/parada; el VFD controla velocidad continuamente","El soft starter controla velocidad y el VFD solo arranque","El VFD es más barato que el soft starter"],"o_en":["They are exactly the same","Soft starter only controls start/stop; VFD controls speed continuously","Soft starter controls speed and VFD only startup","VFD is cheaper than soft starter"],"c":1,"e":"El soft starter solo maneja el arranque y parada suave. El VFD controla la velocidad del motor continuamente durante toda la operación.","e_en":"The soft starter only handles smooth starting and stopping. The VFD controls motor speed continuously throughout operation.","a":"El soft starter solo maneja el arranque y parada suave. El VFD controla la velocidad del motor continuamente durante toda la operación.","a_en":"The soft starter only handles smooth starting and stopping. The VFD controls motor speed continuously throughout operation."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sensor de temperatura de 10KΩ NTC lee 15KΩ a temperatura ambiente de 75°F. ¿Qué indica?","q_en":"A 10KΩ NTC temperature sensor reads 15KΩ at 75°F ambient temperature. What does it indicate?","o":["Sensor funcionando correctamente (NTC sube con temperatura baja)","Sensor defectuoso, lectura demasiado alta para 75°F (debería estar cerca de 10KΩ)","Temperatura realmente más baja de lo indicado","Necesita calibración"],"o_en":["Sensor working correctly (NTC rises with low temperature)","Defective sensor, reading too high for 75°F (should be near 10KΩ)","Temperature actually lower than indicated","Needs calibration"],"c":1,"e":"Un sensor de 10KΩ NTC tiene 10KΩ a 77°F (25°C). A 75°F debería estar muy cerca de 10KΩ. 15KΩ indica sensor defectuoso o desconectado parcialmente.","e_en":"A 10KΩ NTC sensor has 10KΩ at 77°F (25°C). At 75°F it should be very close to 10KΩ. 15KΩ indicates defective or partially disconnected sensor.","a":"Un sensor de 10KΩ NTC tiene 10KΩ a 77°F (25°C). A 75°F debería estar muy cerca de 10KΩ. 15KΩ indica sensor defectuoso o desconectado parcialmente.","a_en":"A 10KΩ NTC sensor has 10KΩ at 77°F (25°C). At 75°F it should be very close to 10KΩ. 15KΩ indicates defective or partially disconnected sensor."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control BACnet utiliza protocolo de comunicación basado en:","q_en":"A BACnet control system uses communication protocol based on:","o":["Solo RS-485","Puede usar Ethernet/IP, MS/TP (RS-485), o WiFi dependiendo de la capa","Solo WiFi","Solo señales analógicas 4-20mA"],"o_en":["Only RS-485","Can use Ethernet/IP, MS/TP (RS-485), or WiFi depending on layer","Only WiFi","Only 4-20mA analog signals"],"c":1,"e":"BACnet soporta múltiples capas físicas: BACnet/IP (Ethernet), MS/TP (RS-485 serial), y otros. La capa depende del nivel del sistema.","e_en":"BACnet supports multiple physical layers: BACnet/IP (Ethernet), MS/TP (RS-485 serial), and others. Layer depends on system level.","a":"BACnet soporta múltiples capas físicas: BACnet/IP (Ethernet), MS/TP (RS-485 serial), y otros. La capa depende del nivel del sistema.","a_en":"BACnet supports multiple physical layers: BACnet/IP (Ethernet), MS/TP (RS-485 serial), and others. Layer depends on system level."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un sistema Modbus RTU, la comunicación serial típica usa configuración:","q_en":"In a Modbus RTU system, typical serial communication uses configuration:","o":["8 bits datos, sin paridad, 1 stop bit (8N1)","9600 baud, 8 bits datos, par paridad, 1 stop bit (9600-8E1)","4800 baud, 7 bits datos, impar paridad","19200 baud, 8 bits datos, sin paridad"],"o_en":["8 data bits, no parity, 1 stop bit (8N1)","9600 baud, 8 data bits, even parity, 1 stop bit (9600-8E1)","4800 baud, 7 data bits, odd parity","19200 baud, 8 data bits, no parity"],"c":1,"e":"La configuración más común de Modbus RTU en HVAC es 9600 baud, 8 bits de datos, paridad par (Even), 1 stop bit.","e_en":"Most common Modbus RTU configuration in HVAC is 9600 baud, 8 data bits, Even parity, 1 stop bit.","a":"La configuración más común de Modbus RTU en HVAC es 9600 baud, 8 bits de datos, paridad par (Even), 1 stop bit.","a_en":"Most common Modbus RTU configuration in HVAC is 9600 baud, 8 data bits, Even parity, 1 stop bit."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Una señal de 4-20mA comparada con una de 0-10VDC tiene la ventaja de:","q_en":"A 4-20mA signal compared to 0-10VDC has the advantage of:","o":["Es más barata de implementar","Es inmune a la caída de voltaje por distancia y un cable roto se detecta inmediatamente (0mA)","Tiene mayor resolución","No necesita fuente de alimentación"],"o_en":["Cheaper to implement","Immune to voltage drop over distance and broken wire is immediately detected (0mA)","Has higher resolution","Doesn't need power supply"],"c":1,"e":"4-20mA no sufre caída de voltaje por distancia y un cable roto = 0mA (detectable). Con 0-10V, un cable roto = 0V que podría confundirse con señal válida.","e_en":"4-20mA doesn't suffer voltage drop over distance and broken wire = 0mA (detectable). With 0-10V, broken wire = 0V which could be confused with valid signal.","a":"4-20mA no sufre caída de voltaje por distancia y un cable roto = 0mA (detectable). Con 0-10V, un cable roto = 0V que podría confundirse con señal válida.","a_en":"4-20mA doesn't suffer voltage drop over distance and broken wire = 0mA (detectable). With 0-10V, broken wire = 0V which could be confused with valid signal."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un actuador de damper recibe señal de 0-10VDC. Si mides 7.5V en el actuador, ¿qué posición tiene el damper?","q_en":"A damper actuator receives 0-10VDC signal. If you measure 7.5V at the actuator, what position is the damper?","o":["50% abierto","75% abierto","25% abierto","100% abierto"],"o_en":["50% open","75% open","25% open","100% open"],"c":1,"e":"7.5V / 10V = 75%. El damper está al 75% de apertura (asumiendo señal proporcional lineal 0-10V = 0-100%).","e_en":"7.5V / 10V = 75%. The damper is at 75% open (assuming linear proportional 0-10V = 0-100% signal).","a":"7.5V / 10V = 75%. El damper está al 75% de apertura (asumiendo señal proporcional lineal 0-10V = 0-100%).","a_en":"7.5V / 10V = 75%. The damper is at 75% open (assuming linear proportional 0-10V = 0-100% signal)."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Una resistencia de terminación de 120Ω en un bus RS-485 se instala:","q_en":"A 120Ω termination resistor on an RS-485 bus is installed:","o":["En cada dispositivo del bus","Solo en los dos extremos físicos del bus","Solo en el controlador maestro","No es necesaria para distancias cortas"],"o_en":["At every device on the bus","Only at the two physical ends of the bus","Only at the master controller","Not needed for short distances"],"c":1,"e":"Las resistencias de terminación de 120Ω se instalan SOLO en los dos extremos físicos del bus RS-485 para prevenir reflexiones de señal.","e_en":"120Ω termination resistors are installed ONLY at the two physical ends of the RS-485 bus to prevent signal reflections.","a":"Las resistencias de terminación de 120Ω se instalan SOLO en los dos extremos físicos del bus RS-485 para prevenir reflexiones de señal.","a_en":"120Ω termination resistors are installed ONLY at the two physical ends of the RS-485 bus to prevent signal reflections."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un relé de falla de fase (phase failure relay) protege un motor trifásico contra:","q_en":"A phase failure relay protects a three-phase motor against:","o":["Solo sobrevoltaje","Pérdida de fase, inversión de fase y desbalance de voltaje","Solo bajo voltaje","Solo sobrecarga de corriente"],"o_en":["Only overvoltage","Phase loss, phase reversal and voltage imbalance","Only low voltage","Only current overload"],"c":1,"e":"Un relé de falla de fase monitorea las tres fases y protege contra: pérdida de una fase, inversión de secuencia de fases, y desbalance excesivo.","e_en":"A phase failure relay monitors all three phases and protects against: single phase loss, phase sequence reversal, and excessive imbalance.","a":"Un relé de falla de fase monitorea las tres fases y protege contra: pérdida de una fase, inversión de secuencia de fases, y desbalance excesivo.","a_en":"A phase failure relay monitors all three phases and protects against: single phase loss, phase sequence reversal, and excessive imbalance."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de iluminación UV-C para desinfección del serpentín del evaporador debe instalarse:","q_en":"A UV-C lighting system for evaporator coil disinfection should be installed:","o":["Antes del filtro de aire","Directo sobre el serpentín del evaporador, con línea de vista al serpentín","Después del ventilador, en el plenum de suministro","En el ducto de retorno"],"o_en":["Before the air filter","Directly on the evaporator coil, with line of sight to the coil","After the blower, in the supply plenum","In the return duct"],"c":1,"e":"La luz UV-C para serpentín debe tener línea de vista directa al serpentín del evaporador para máxima efectividad en eliminar moho y bacterias.","e_en":"UV-C light for coil must have direct line of sight to evaporator coil for maximum effectiveness in eliminating mold and bacteria.","a":"La luz UV-C para serpentín debe tener línea de vista directa al serpentín del evaporador para máxima efectividad en eliminar moho y bacterias.","a_en":"UV-C light for coil must have direct line of sight to evaporator coil for maximum effectiveness in eliminating mold and bacteria."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sensor de presión diferencial para medir flujo de aire en ductos usa un rango típico de:","q_en":"A differential pressure sensor for measuring duct airflow uses a typical range of:","o":["0-5 PSI","0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa)","0-10 inwc","0-100 Pa"],"o_en":["0-5 PSI","0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa)","0-10 inwc","0-100 Pa"],"c":1,"e":"Los sensores de presión diferencial para ductos típicamente miden 0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa), el rango normal de presión estática en ductos residenciales/comerciales.","e_en":"Differential pressure sensors for ducts typically measure 0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa), the normal static pressure range in residential/commercial ducts.","a":"Los sensores de presión diferencial para ductos típicamente miden 0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa), el rango normal de presión estática en ductos residenciales/comerciales.","a_en":"Differential pressure sensors for ducts typically measure 0-1 inwc (0-250 Pa), the normal static pressure range in residential/commercial ducts."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sensor CO2 en un sistema de ventilación bajo demanda (DCV) mantiene niveles interiores por debajo de:","q_en":"A CO2 sensor in a demand control ventilation (DCV) system maintains indoor levels below:","o":["400 ppm","1,000 ppm","2,000 ppm","800 ppm"],"o_en":["400 ppm","1,000 ppm","2,000 ppm","800 ppm"],"c":1,"e":"ASHRAE 62.1 recomienda mantener CO2 interior por debajo de 1,000 ppm (700 ppm sobre exterior). 400 ppm es el nivel exterior normal.","e_en":"ASHRAE 62.1 recommends maintaining indoor CO2 below 1,000 ppm (700 ppm above outdoor). 400 ppm is normal outdoor level.","a":"ASHRAE 62.1 recomienda mantener CO2 interior por debajo de 1,000 ppm (700 ppm sobre exterior). 400 ppm es el nivel exterior normal.","a_en":"ASHRAE 62.1 recommends maintaining indoor CO2 below 1,000 ppm (700 ppm above outdoor). 400 ppm is normal outdoor level."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al conectar un VFD, el cable entre el VFD y el motor debe ser:","q_en":"When connecting a VFD, the cable between VFD and motor should be:","o":["Cualquier cable estándar THHN","Cable apantallado/blindado (shielded) para reducir interferencia electromagnética","Cable de menor calibre que el alimentador","Cable sin blindaje para mejor ventilación"],"o_en":["Any standard THHN cable","Shielded cable to reduce electromagnetic interference","Smaller gauge than feeder cable","Unshielded cable for better ventilation"],"c":1,"e":"El VFD genera ondas PWM que causan interferencia electromagnética. Cable blindado entre VFD y motor reduce EMI y protege equipos cercanos.","e_en":"VFD generates PWM waves causing electromagnetic interference. Shielded cable between VFD and motor reduces EMI and protects nearby equipment.","a":"El VFD genera ondas PWM que causan interferencia electromagnética. Cable blindado entre VFD y motor reduce EMI y protege equipos cercanos.","a_en":"VFD generates PWM waves causing electromagnetic interference. Shielded cable between VFD and motor reduces EMI and protects nearby equipment."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control con protocolo LonWorks usa topología de red tipo:","q_en":"A LonWorks protocol control system uses network topology of type:","o":["Solo estrella","Libre (free topology) - bus, estrella, anillo o combinación","Solo bus lineal","Solo anillo"],"o_en":["Star only","Free topology - bus, star, ring or combination","Linear bus only","Ring only"],"c":1,"e":"LonWorks soporta topología libre: puede ser bus, estrella, anillo o cualquier combinación. Es una de sus ventajas sobre otros protocolos.","e_en":"LonWorks supports free topology: can be bus, star, ring or any combination. It's one of its advantages over other protocols.","a":"LonWorks soporta topología libre: puede ser bus, estrella, anillo o cualquier combinación. Es una de sus ventajas sobre otros protocolos.","a_en":"LonWorks supports free topology: can be bus, star, ring or any combination. It's one of its advantages over other protocols."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un contactor con bobina de 24VAC marca 'inrush' de 70VA y 'sealed' de 12VA. ¿Qué significan estos valores?","q_en":"A contactor with 24VAC coil marked 'inrush' 70VA and 'sealed' 12VA. What do these values mean?","o":["Son los valores de corriente de la carga","Inrush es la potencia para jalar la armadura; sealed es la potencia para mantenerla cerrada","Inrush es la potencia del motor; sealed es la del ventilador","Son los valores máximos de potencia de la carga"],"o_en":["They are load current values","Inrush is power to pull the armature; sealed is power to keep it closed","Inrush is motor power; sealed is fan power","They are maximum load power values"],"c":1,"e":"La bobina necesita más potencia para jalar inicialmente (inrush=70VA) que para mantenerse cerrada (sealed=12VA). Es importante para dimensionar el transformador.","e_en":"The coil needs more power to initially pull in (inrush=70VA) than to stay closed (sealed=12VA). Important for transformer sizing.","a":"La bobina necesita más potencia para jalar inicialmente (inrush=70VA) que para mantenerse cerrada (sealed=12VA). Es importante para dimensionar el transformador.","a_en":"The coil needs more power to initially pull in (inrush=70VA) than to stay closed (sealed=12VA). Important for transformer sizing."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Si mides 28VAC en los terminales de una bobina de contactor de 24V y el contactor NO jala, pero mides continuidad en la bobina (2Ω), ¿cuál es el problema?","q_en":"If you measure 28VAC at a 24V contactor coil terminals and the contactor does NOT pull in, but you measure continuity on the coil (2Ω), what is the problem?","o":["Bobina defectuosa","Contactor mecánicamente trabado o con armadura corroída/pegada","Voltaje demasiado alto","Transformador débil"],"o_en":["Defective coil","Contactor mechanically stuck or with corroded/stuck armature","Voltage too high","Weak transformer"],"c":1,"e":"Si la bobina tiene continuidad y voltaje adecuado pero no jala, el problema es mecánico: armadura pegada, corrosión, resorte demasiado fuerte, o obstrucción.","e_en":"If coil has continuity and adequate voltage but won't pull in, the problem is mechanical: stuck armature, corrosion, spring too strong, or obstruction.","a":"Si la bobina tiene continuidad y voltaje adecuado pero no jala, el problema es mecánico: armadura pegada, corrosión, resorte demasiado fuerte, o obstrucción.","a_en":"If coil has continuity and adequate voltage but won't pull in, the problem is mechanical: stuck armature, corrosion, spring too strong, or obstruction."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un circuito de 24V tiene un fusible de 3A que se quema al energizar el contactor. La bobina del contactor consume normalmente 0.5A sellada. El problema probable es:","q_en":"A 24V circuit has a 3A fuse that blows when energizing the contactor. The contactor coil normally draws 0.5A sealed. The probable problem is:","o":["Fusible subdimensionado","La corriente inrush de la bobina excede 3A momentáneamente; necesitas fusible de retardo o verificar cortocircuito","Bobina en cortocircuito","Transformador sobredimensionado"],"o_en":["Undersized fuse","Coil inrush current momentarily exceeds 3A; need time-delay fuse or check for short","Shorted coil","Oversized transformer"],"c":1,"e":"Las bobinas de contactor tienen alto inrush (puede ser 5-10× sealed). Si el fusible es rápido, se funde con el pico. Verifica si hay corto y considera fusible de retardo.","e_en":"Contactor coils have high inrush (can be 5-10× sealed). If fuse is fast-blow, it melts from the spike. Check for short and consider time-delay fuse.","a":"Las bobinas de contactor tienen alto inrush (puede ser 5-10× sealed). Si el fusible es rápido, se funde con el pico. Verifica si hay corto y considera fusible de retardo.","a_en":"Contactor coils have high inrush (can be 5-10× sealed). If fuse is fast-blow, it melts from the spike. Check for short and consider time-delay fuse."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de calefacción con resistencias eléctricas de 15kW a 240V tiene un secuenciador con 3 etapas de 5kW cada una. El amperaje por etapa es:","q_en":"A 15kW electric heat system at 240V has a sequencer with 3 stages of 5kW each. The amperage per stage is:","o":["15.5A","20.8A","25.0A","18.2A"],"o_en":["15.5A","20.8A","25.0A","18.2A"],"c":1,"e":"Por etapa: I = P/V = 5,000/240 = 20.83A ≈ 20.8A por etapa.","e_en":"Per stage: I = P/V = 5,000/240 = 20.83A ≈ 20.8A per stage.","a":"Por etapa: I = P/V = 5,000/240 = 20.83A ≈ 20.8A por etapa.","a_en":"Per stage: I = P/V = 5,000/240 = 20.83A ≈ 20.8A per stage."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Para verificar si un secuenciador está funcionando, mides voltaje en sus terminales de salida al activar calefacción. ¿Cuánto tiempo esperas para la primera etapa?","q_en":"To verify a sequencer is working, you measure voltage at its output terminals when activating heat. How long do you wait for the first stage?","o":["Inmediatamente (0 segundos)","15-30 segundos","2-3 minutos","5 minutos"],"o_en":["Immediately (0 seconds)","15-30 seconds","2-3 minutes","5 minutes"],"c":1,"e":"Los secuenciadores activan la primera etapa en 15-30 segundos y las siguientes cada 15-30 segundos adicionales para escalonar la demanda.","e_en":"Sequencers activate the first stage in 15-30 seconds and subsequent stages every 15-30 additional seconds to stagger demand.","a":"Los secuenciadores activan la primera etapa en 15-30 segundos y las siguientes cada 15-30 segundos adicionales para escalonar la demanda.","a_en":"Sequencers activate the first stage in 15-30 seconds and subsequent stages every 15-30 additional seconds to stagger demand."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sail switch (interruptor de flujo de aire) en un air handler con resistencias eléctricas se abre cuando:","q_en":"A sail switch (airflow switch) on an air handler with heat strips opens when:","o":["El flujo de aire es excesivo","No hay flujo de aire suficiente (protección contra sobrecalentamiento)","La temperatura del aire es demasiado alta","El motor del ventilador está a velocidad alta"],"o_en":["Airflow is excessive","There's insufficient airflow (overheating protection)","Air temperature is too high","Blower motor is at high speed"],"c":1,"e":"El sail switch es normalmente cerrado con flujo de aire y se abre si no hay flujo suficiente, cortando las resistencias para prevenir sobrecalentamiento y fuego.","e_en":"The sail switch is normally closed with airflow and opens if insufficient airflow, cutting heat strips to prevent overheating and fire.","a":"El sail switch es normalmente cerrado con flujo de aire y se abre si no hay flujo suficiente, cortando las resistencias para prevenir sobrecalentamiento y fuego.","a_en":"The sail switch is normally closed with airflow and opens if insufficient airflow, cutting heat strips to prevent overheating and fire."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un limit switch (interruptor de límite) de temperatura en el plenum de suministro de un air handler se abre a aproximadamente:","q_en":"A temperature limit switch in the supply plenum of an air handler opens at approximately:","o":["120°F","200°F","160°F","250°F"],"o_en":["120°F","200°F","160°F","250°F"],"c":2,"e":"Los limit switches en air handlers eléctricos típicamente se abren alrededor de 160-180°F para prevenir sobrecalentamiento del plenum.","e_en":"Limit switches on electric air handlers typically open around 160-180°F to prevent plenum overheating.","a":"Los limit switches en air handlers eléctricos típicamente se abren alrededor de 160-180°F para prevenir sobrecalentamiento del plenum.","a_en":"Limit switches on electric air handlers typically open around 160-180°F to prevent plenum overheating."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema con protocolo Modbus tiene dirección de esclavo 0. ¿Es esto válido?","q_en":"A Modbus system has slave address 0. Is this valid?","o":["Sí, es la primera dirección disponible","No, la dirección 0 es broadcast (todos los dispositivos); las direcciones válidas son 1-247","Sí, pero solo para el maestro","No, las direcciones empiezan en 10"],"o_en":["Yes, it's the first available address","No, address 0 is broadcast (all devices); valid addresses are 1-247","Yes, but only for the master","No, addresses start at 10"],"c":1,"e":"En Modbus, la dirección 0 es reservada para broadcast. Las direcciones válidas de esclavos son 1 a 247. 248-255 son reservadas.","e_en":"In Modbus, address 0 is reserved for broadcast. Valid slave addresses are 1 to 247. 248-255 are reserved.","a":"En Modbus, la dirección 0 es reservada para broadcast. Las direcciones válidas de esclavos son 1 a 247. 248-255 son reservadas.","a_en":"In Modbus, address 0 is reserved for broadcast. Valid slave addresses are 1 to 247. 248-255 are reserved."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control PID tiene respuesta oscilatoria. ¿Qué parámetro debes ajustar primero?","q_en":"A PID control system has oscillatory response. Which parameter should you adjust first?","o":["Aumentar la ganancia integral (I)","Reducir la ganancia proporcional (P)","Aumentar la ganancia derivativa (D)","Reducir todos los parámetros a la mitad"],"o_en":["Increase integral gain (I)","Reduce proportional gain (P)","Increase derivative gain (D)","Reduce all parameters by half"],"c":1,"e":"Oscilación generalmente indica ganancia proporcional demasiado alta. Reducir P es el primer paso para estabilizar la respuesta.","e_en":"Oscillation generally indicates proportional gain too high. Reducing P is the first step to stabilize the response.","a":"Oscilación generalmente indica ganancia proporcional demasiado alta. Reducir P es el primer paso para estabilizar la respuesta.","a_en":"Oscillation generally indicates proportional gain too high. Reducing P is the first step to stabilize the response."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un capacitor de 45 MFD 440VAC necesita reemplazo pero solo tienes 50 MFD 370VAC disponible. ¿Puedes usarlo?","q_en":"A 45 MFD 440VAC capacitor needs replacement but you only have 50 MFD 370VAC available. Can you use it?","o":["Sí, el MFD más alto compensa el voltaje más bajo","No, el voltaje del reemplazo debe ser igual o mayor al original (370 < 440)","Sí, ambos valores están dentro de tolerancia","No, el MFD debe ser exacto"],"o_en":["Yes, higher MFD compensates for lower voltage","No, replacement voltage must be equal or higher than original (370 < 440)","Yes, both values are within tolerance","No, MFD must be exact"],"c":1,"e":"Nunca uses un capacitor con voltaje MENOR. 370VAC < 440VAC original. El capacitor puede fallar prematuramente o explotar. El MFD puede variar ±10%.","e_en":"Never use a capacitor with LOWER voltage rating. 370VAC < 440VAC original. The capacitor may fail prematurely or explode. MFD can vary ±10%.","a":"Nunca uses un capacitor con voltaje MENOR. 370VAC < 440VAC original. El capacitor puede fallar prematuramente o explotar. El MFD puede variar ±10%.","a_en":"Never use a capacitor with LOWER voltage rating. 370VAC < 440VAC original. The capacitor may fail prematurely or explode. MFD can vary ±10%."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un compresor scroll monofásico tiene datos de placa: 208-230V, RLA 20A. Mides 195V en las terminales. ¿Es aceptable operar?","q_en":"A single-phase scroll compressor has nameplate data: 208-230V, RLA 20A. You measure 195V at terminals. Is it acceptable to operate?","o":["Sí, está dentro del rango del compresor","No, está por debajo del rango mínimo (208V - 10% = 187V... pero 195V puede causar sobrecalentamiento)","Sí, 195V es suficiente para un scroll","No, necesita exactamente 208V mínimo"],"o_en":["Yes, within compressor range","No, below minimum range (208V - 10% = 187V... but 195V can cause overheating)","Yes, 195V is sufficient for a scroll","No, needs exactly 208V minimum"],"c":1,"e":"Aunque 195V está técnicamente en el rango -10% de 208V, está bajo. El compresor consumirá más amperaje, se sobrecalentará y la vida útil se reduce significativamente.","e_en":"Although 195V is technically within -10% of 208V, it's low. Compressor will draw more amperage, overheat and lifespan is significantly reduced.","a":"Aunque 195V está técnicamente en el rango -10% de 208V, está bajo. El compresor consumirá más amperaje, se sobrecalentará y la vida útil se reduce significativamente.","a_en":"Although 195V is technically within -10% of 208V, it's low. Compressor will draw more amperage, overheat and lifespan is significantly reduced."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al conectar un termostato WiFi que necesita cable C, pero el sistema solo tiene 4 cables (R, G, Y, W), la solución correcta es:","q_en":"When installing a WiFi thermostat that needs a C wire, but the system only has 4 wires (R, G, Y, W), the correct solution is:","o":["Usar el cable G como C y perder control independiente del ventilador","Instalar un add-a-wire (adaptador) o pasar un cable adicional","Conectar C al cable de tierra","Los termostatos WiFi no necesitan cable C"],"o_en":["Use G wire as C and lose independent fan control","Install an add-a-wire (adapter) or run an additional wire","Connect C to ground wire","WiFi thermostats don't need C wire"],"c":1,"e":"La solución correcta es un add-a-wire/adaptador que permite usar los 4 cables existentes para las 5 funciones necesarias, o pasar un cable nuevo.","e_en":"The correct solution is an add-a-wire/adapter that allows using the 4 existing wires for the 5 needed functions, or running a new wire.","a":"La solución correcta es un add-a-wire/adaptador que permite usar los 4 cables existentes para las 5 funciones necesarias, o pasar un cable nuevo.","a_en":"The correct solution is an add-a-wire/adapter that allows using the 4 existing wires for the 5 needed functions, or running a new wire."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control usa un relay SPDT para alternar entre calefacción y enfriamiento. Las terminales son COM, NO y NC. Para enfriamiento (Y), ¿dónde conectas?","q_en":"A control system uses an SPDT relay to alternate between heating and cooling. Terminals are COM, NO and NC. For cooling (Y), where do you connect?","o":["COM y NC (normalmente cerrado)","COM y NO (normalmente abierto) - se activa cuando la bobina se energiza","NC y NO juntos","Solo a COM"],"o_en":["COM and NC (normally closed)","COM and NO (normally open) - activates when coil is energized","NC and NO together","Only to COM"],"c":1,"e":"Para enfriamiento activo, se conecta al contacto NO. Cuando la bobina se energiza, COM conecta a NO activando enfriamiento. NC queda para calefacción default.","e_en":"For active cooling, connect to NO contact. When coil energizes, COM connects to NO activating cooling. NC remains for default heating.","a":"Para enfriamiento activo, se conecta al contacto NO. Cuando la bobina se energiza, COM conecta a NO activando enfriamiento. NC queda para calefacción default.","a_en":"For active cooling, connect to NO contact. When coil energizes, COM connects to NO activating cooling. NC remains for default heating."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al usar un osciloscopio para diagnosticar la señal de salida de un VFD, la forma de onda al motor es:","q_en":"When using an oscilloscope to diagnose VFD output signal, the waveform to the motor is:","o":["Sinusoidal pura como la de la red eléctrica","PWM (modulación de ancho de pulso) que simula una sinusoidal","Cuadrada a frecuencia fija","Triangular a frecuencia variable"],"o_en":["Pure sinusoidal like the power grid","PWM (pulse width modulation) that simulates a sinusoidal","Square wave at fixed frequency","Triangular at variable frequency"],"c":1,"e":"El VFD produce una onda PWM (pulsos de voltaje DC) que el motor interpreta como sinusoidal por su inductancia. No es una onda sinusoidal pura.","e_en":"The VFD produces a PWM wave (DC voltage pulses) that the motor interprets as sinusoidal due to its inductance. Not a pure sinusoidal wave.","a":"El VFD produce una onda PWM (pulsos de voltaje DC) que el motor interpreta como sinusoidal por su inductancia. No es una onda sinusoidal pura.","a_en":"The VFD produces a PWM wave (DC voltage pulses) that the motor interprets as sinusoidal due to its inductance. Not a pure sinusoidal wave."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor de 460V alimentado por VFD presenta fallas prematuras de aislamiento. La causa probable es:","q_en":"A 460V motor fed by a VFD has premature insulation failures. The probable cause is:","o":["Voltaje del VFD demasiado bajo","Picos de voltaje (voltage spikes) del PWM del VFD que degradan el aislamiento del motor","Motor sobredimensionado para la carga","Frecuencia de operación demasiado baja"],"o_en":["VFD voltage too low","PWM voltage spikes from VFD that degrade motor insulation","Motor oversized for the load","Operating frequency too low"],"c":1,"e":"Los pulsos PWM del VFD crean picos de voltaje que pueden exceder 2× el voltaje nominal, degradando el aislamiento del motor prematuramente. Se recomienda motores inverter-rated.","e_en":"VFD PWM pulses create voltage spikes that can exceed 2× rated voltage, degrading motor insulation prematurely. Inverter-rated motors are recommended.","a":"Los pulsos PWM del VFD crean picos de voltaje que pueden exceder 2× el voltaje nominal, degradando el aislamiento del motor prematuramente. Se recomienda motores inverter-rated.","a_en":"VFD PWM pulses create voltage spikes that can exceed 2× rated voltage, degrading motor insulation prematurely. Inverter-rated motors are recommended."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al instalar un filtro de línea (line reactor) en la entrada de un VFD, este protege contra:","q_en":"When installing a line reactor at the input of a VFD, it protects against:","o":["Sobrecalentamiento del motor","Armónicos devueltos a la red eléctrica y picos de voltaje de entrada","Cortocircuitos en el motor","Pérdida de fase"],"o_en":["Motor overheating","Harmonics fed back to power grid and input voltage spikes","Motor short circuits","Phase loss"],"c":1,"e":"El reactor de línea reduce armónicos que el VFD devuelve a la red y protege al VFD de picos de voltaje transitorios de la alimentación.","e_en":"The line reactor reduces harmonics the VFD feeds back to the grid and protects the VFD from transient voltage spikes from the power supply.","a":"El reactor de línea reduce armónicos que el VFD devuelve a la red y protege al VFD de picos de voltaje transitorios de la alimentación.","a_en":"The line reactor reduces harmonics the VFD feeds back to the grid and protects the VFD from transient voltage spikes from the power supply."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor trifásico conectado en estrella (Y) a 460V puede reconectarse en delta (Δ) para operar a:","q_en":"A three-phase motor connected in star (Y) at 460V can be reconnected in delta (Δ) to operate at:","o":["460V","265V (460/√3)","230V","208V"],"o_en":["460V","265V (460/√3)","230V","208V"],"c":1,"e":"La relación Y a Δ es √3 (1.732). Si el motor es 460V en Y, en Delta opera a 460/1.732 = 265V. Solo si está diseñado como dual voltage.","e_en":"Y to Δ ratio is √3 (1.732). If motor is 460V in Y, in Delta it operates at 460/1.732 = 265V. Only if designed as dual voltage.","a":"La relación Y a Δ es √3 (1.732). Si el motor es 460V en Y, en Delta opera a 460/1.732 = 265V. Solo si está diseñado como dual voltage.","a_en":"Y to Δ ratio is √3 (1.732). If motor is 460V in Y, in Delta it operates at 460/1.732 = 265V. Only if designed as dual voltage."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor dual voltage 230/460V tiene 9 cables (T1-T9). Para conectar a 460V (alto voltaje), ¿cómo se conectan los devanados?","q_en":"A 230/460V dual voltage motor has 9 leads (T1-T9). To connect for 460V (high voltage), how are windings connected?","o":["En paralelo (Delta)","En serie (Estrella/Y)","Mezcla de serie y paralelo","No importa la configuración a 460V"],"o_en":["In parallel (Delta)","In series (Star/Y)","Mix of series and parallel","Configuration doesn't matter at 460V"],"c":1,"e":"Para alto voltaje (460V), los devanados se conectan en serie (Y). Para bajo voltaje (230V), se conectan en paralelo (Δ).","e_en":"For high voltage (460V), windings connect in series (Y). For low voltage (230V), they connect in parallel (Δ).","a":"Para alto voltaje (460V), los devanados se conectan en serie (Y). Para bajo voltaje (230V), se conectan en paralelo (Δ).","a_en":"For high voltage (460V), windings connect in series (Y). For low voltage (230V), they connect in parallel (Δ)."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un circuito de 480V trifásico alimenta un transformador de 480V-208/120V. Si la carga total es 50 kVA, ¿cuál es la corriente en el secundario?","q_en":"A 480V three-phase circuit feeds a 480V-208/120V transformer. If total load is 50 kVA, what is the secondary current?","o":["120A","139A","208A","100A"],"o_en":["120A","139A","208A","100A"],"c":1,"e":"I = kVA × 1000 / (√3 × V) = 50,000 / (1.732 × 208) = 50,000 / 360.3 = 138.8A ≈ 139A.","e_en":"I = kVA × 1000 / (√3 × V) = 50,000 / (1.732 × 208) = 50,000 / 360.3 = 138.8A ≈ 139A.","a":"I = kVA × 1000 / (√3 × V) = 50,000 / (1.732 × 208) = 50,000 / 360.3 = 138.8A ≈ 139A.","a_en":"I = kVA × 1000 / (√3 × V) = 50,000 / (1.732 × 208) = 50,000 / 360.3 = 138.8A ≈ 139A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de 208V trifásico tiene voltaje medido entre fase y neutro de:","q_en":"A 208V three-phase system has voltage measured between phase and neutral of:","o":["208V","120V","104V","240V"],"o_en":["208V","120V","104V","240V"],"c":1,"e":"En un sistema 208Y/120V, el voltaje fase-neutro = 208/√3 = 120V. El 208V es fase-fase.","e_en":"In a 208Y/120V system, phase-neutral voltage = 208/√3 = 120V. 208V is phase-to-phase.","a":"En un sistema 208Y/120V, el voltaje fase-neutro = 208/√3 = 120V. El 208V es fase-fase.","a_en":"In a 208Y/120V system, phase-neutral voltage = 208/√3 = 120V. 208V is phase-to-phase."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un panel de distribución dice '480Y/277V'. ¿Qué voltaje obtienes entre una fase y neutro?","q_en":"A distribution panel reads '480Y/277V'. What voltage do you get between one phase and neutral?","o":["480V","277V","240V","120V"],"o_en":["480V","277V","240V","120V"],"c":1,"e":"En 480Y/277V: fase-fase = 480V, fase-neutro = 277V (480/√3). 277V se usa para iluminación comercial.","e_en":"In 480Y/277V: phase-phase = 480V, phase-neutral = 277V (480/√3). 277V is used for commercial lighting.","a":"En 480Y/277V: fase-fase = 480V, fase-neutro = 277V (480/√3). 277V se usa para iluminación comercial.","a_en":"In 480Y/277V: phase-phase = 480V, phase-neutral = 277V (480/√3). 277V is used for commercial lighting."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un transformador de aislamiento (isolation transformer) 1:1 en un circuito de control HVAC sirve para:","q_en":"An isolation transformer 1:1 in an HVAC control circuit serves to:","o":["Duplicar el voltaje","Aislar eléctricamente los circuitos y eliminar ruido/interferencia entre fuentes de poder","Reducir el voltaje a la mitad","No tiene función útil con relación 1:1"],"o_en":["Double the voltage","Electrically isolate circuits and eliminate noise/interference between power sources","Reduce voltage by half","Has no useful function at 1:1 ratio"],"c":1,"e":"Un transformador 1:1 no cambia voltaje pero aísla galvánicamente los circuitos, eliminando loops de tierra y ruido eléctrico.","e_en":"A 1:1 transformer doesn't change voltage but galvanically isolates circuits, eliminating ground loops and electrical noise.","a":"Un transformador 1:1 no cambia voltaje pero aísla galvánicamente los circuitos, eliminando loops de tierra y ruido eléctrico.","a_en":"A 1:1 transformer doesn't change voltage but galvanically isolates circuits, eliminating ground loops and electrical noise."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply) para un controlador DDC debe dimensionarse considerando:","q_en":"A UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply) for a DDC controller should be sized considering:","o":["Solo la potencia del controlador","Potencia total del controlador + todos los actuadores y sensores alimentados, más 20% de margen","Solo la potencia del actuador más grande","El doble de la potencia del controlador"],"o_en":["Only controller power","Total power of controller + all powered actuators and sensors, plus 20% margin","Only the largest actuator's power","Double the controller power"],"c":1,"e":"El UPS debe cubrir el controlador más todas las cargas alimentadas por él (actuadores, sensores, módulos de comunicación) más margen de seguridad.","e_en":"The UPS must cover the controller plus all loads powered by it (actuators, sensors, communication modules) plus safety margin.","a":"El UPS debe cubrir el controlador más todas las cargas alimentadas por él (actuadores, sensores, módulos de comunicación) más margen de seguridad.","a_en":"The UPS must cover the controller plus all loads powered by it (actuators, sensors, communication modules) plus safety margin."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor de 3HP, 208V trifásico con eficiencia del 89% y factor de potencia de 0.82. ¿Cuál es la corriente de línea?","q_en":"A 3HP, 208V three-phase motor with 89% efficiency and 0.82 power factor. What is the line current?","o":["7.2A","8.6A","10.1A","6.5A"],"o_en":["7.2A","8.6A","10.1A","6.5A"],"c":1,"e":"3HP = 2,238W. Con eficiencia: 2,238/0.89 = 2,514W entrada. I = P/(√3 × V × PF) = 2,514/(1.732 × 208 × 0.82) = 8.51A ≈ 8.6A.","e_en":"3HP = 2,238W. With efficiency: 2,238/0.89 = 2,514W input. I = P/(√3 × V × PF) = 2,514/(1.732 × 208 × 0.82) = 8.51A ≈ 8.6A.","a":"3HP = 2,238W. Con eficiencia: 2,238/0.89 = 2,514W entrada. I = P/(√3 × V × PF) = 2,514/(1.732 × 208 × 0.82) = 8.51A ≈ 8.6A.","a_en":"3HP = 2,238W. With efficiency: 2,238/0.89 = 2,514W input. I = P/(√3 × V × PF) = 2,514/(1.732 × 208 × 0.82) = 8.51A ≈ 8.6A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La resistencia de un cable de cobre AUMENTA cuando:","q_en":"Copper wire resistance INCREASES when:","o":["La temperatura del cable disminuye","La temperatura del cable aumenta","Se aplica mayor voltaje","Se reduce la corriente"],"o_en":["Wire temperature decreases","Wire temperature increases","Higher voltage is applied","Current is reduced"],"c":1,"e":"El cobre tiene coeficiente de temperatura positivo. A mayor temperatura, mayor resistencia. Por eso las conexiones flojas se calientan progresivamente.","e_en":"Copper has positive temperature coefficient. Higher temperature means higher resistance. That's why loose connections progressively heat up.","a":"El cobre tiene coeficiente de temperatura positivo. A mayor temperatura, mayor resistencia. Por eso las conexiones flojas se calientan progresivamente.","a_en":"Copper has positive temperature coefficient. Higher temperature means higher resistance. That's why loose connections progressively heat up."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Una conexión floja en un terminal de breaker causa progresivamente más calor porque:","q_en":"A loose connection at a breaker terminal causes progressively more heat because:","o":["La corriente aumenta con la temperatura","Mayor resistencia del contacto → más calor → más resistencia → más calor (ciclo térmico)","El breaker se desgasta más rápido","El cable se expande y cierra mejor"],"o_en":["Current increases with temperature","Higher contact resistance → more heat → more resistance → more heat (thermal cycle)","Breaker wears faster","Wire expands and seals better"],"c":1,"e":"Conexión floja = alta resistencia de contacto = calor. El calor oxida el cobre = más resistencia = más calor. Ciclo que termina en falla o fuego.","e_en":"Loose connection = high contact resistance = heat. Heat oxidizes copper = more resistance = more heat. Cycle that ends in failure or fire.","a":"Conexión floja = alta resistencia de contacto = calor. El calor oxida el cobre = más resistencia = más calor. Ciclo que termina en falla o fuego.","a_en":"Loose connection = high contact resistance = heat. Heat oxidizes copper = more resistance = more heat. Cycle that ends in failure or fire."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Una cámara termográfica (infrared) detecta un punto caliente en un breaker de un panel. La diferencia de temperatura con breakers adyacentes es 30°F. ¿Cuál es la severidad?","q_en":"A thermal (infrared) camera detects a hot spot on a panel breaker. Temperature difference with adjacent breakers is 30°F. What is the severity?","o":["Normal, no requiere acción","Seria, requiere reparación programada pronto","Crítica, requiere acción inmediata","Menor, monitorear en próxima inspección"],"o_en":["Normal, no action needed","Serious, requires scheduled repair soon","Critical, requires immediate action","Minor, monitor at next inspection"],"c":1,"e":"Una diferencia de 20-40°F sobre componentes similares es seria (NETA MTS). Requiere reparación programada. >40°F es crítica (acción inmediata).","e_en":"A 20-40°F difference over similar components is serious (NETA MTS). Requires scheduled repair. >40°F is critical (immediate action).","a":"Una diferencia de 20-40°F sobre componentes similares es seria (NETA MTS). Requiere reparación programada. >40°F es crítica (acción inmediata).","a_en":"A 20-40°F difference over similar components is serious (NETA MTS). Requires scheduled repair. >40°F is critical (immediate action)."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un circuito de control 0-10VDC para un actuador de damper muestra 10V constante sin importar la señal del controlador. ¿Cuál es la causa?","q_en":"A 0-10VDC control circuit for a damper actuator shows constant 10V regardless of controller signal. What is the cause?","o":["Controlador enviando señal máxima","Cable de señal en cortocircuito con cable de alimentación, o salida del controlador dañada","Actuador trabado en posición abierta","Señal de control invertida"],"o_en":["Controller sending maximum signal","Signal wire shorted to power wire, or damaged controller output","Actuator stuck in open position","Control signal reversed"],"c":1,"e":"10V constante sin variación sugiere que el cable de señal está tocando la alimentación de 10V, o la salida del controlador está dañada en alto.","e_en":"Constant 10V without variation suggests signal wire is touching the 10V supply, or controller output is damaged at high.","a":"10V constante sin variación sugiere que el cable de señal está tocando la alimentación de 10V, o la salida del controlador está dañada en alto.","a_en":"Constant 10V without variation suggests signal wire is touching the 10V supply, or controller output is damaged at high."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Para calibrar un sensor de presión de 4-20mA con rango 0-200 PSI, a 0 PSI debes medir:","q_en":"To calibrate a 4-20mA pressure sensor with 0-200 PSI range, at 0 PSI you should measure:","o":["0 mA","4 mA","10 mA","2 mA"],"o_en":["0 mA","4 mA","10 mA","2 mA"],"c":1,"e":"En señal 4-20mA, el 4mA corresponde al punto cero (0 PSI). 20mA = rango máximo. 0mA indicaría cable roto.","e_en":"In 4-20mA signal, 4mA corresponds to zero point (0 PSI). 20mA = maximum range. 0mA would indicate broken wire.","a":"En señal 4-20mA, el 4mA corresponde al punto cero (0 PSI). 20mA = rango máximo. 0mA indicaría cable roto.","a_en":"In 4-20mA signal, 4mA corresponds to zero point (0 PSI). 20mA = maximum range. 0mA would indicate broken wire."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un relé de enclavamiento (latching relay) se diferencia de un relé normal porque:","q_en":"A latching relay differs from a normal relay because:","o":["Tiene más contactos de potencia","Mantiene su última posición sin energía continua en la bobina","Es más grande y maneja más amperaje","Tiene protección térmica incorporada"],"o_en":["Has more power contacts","Maintains its last position without continuous coil power","Is larger and handles more amperage","Has built-in thermal protection"],"c":1,"e":"Un relé de enclavamiento tiene un mecanismo que mantiene la posición (abierto o cerrado) sin necesitar energía continua. Se usa en circuitos de alarma/seguridad.","e_en":"A latching relay has a mechanism that maintains position (open or closed) without needing continuous power. Used in alarm/safety circuits.","a":"Un relé de enclavamiento tiene un mecanismo que mantiene la posición (abierto o cerrado) sin necesitar energía continua. Se usa en circuitos de alarma/seguridad.","a_en":"A latching relay has a mechanism that maintains position (open or closed) without needing continuous power. Used in alarm/safety circuits."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un chiller enfriado por agua, el arrancador estrella-delta reduce la corriente de arranque a aproximadamente:","q_en":"In a water-cooled chiller, the star-delta starter reduces starting current to approximately:","o":["50% del LRA","33% del LRA (1/3)","25% del LRA","75% del LRA"],"o_en":["50% of LRA","33% of LRA (1/3)","25% of LRA","75% of LRA"],"c":1,"e":"Un arrancador estrella-delta reduce la corriente de arranque a 1/3 (33%) del LRA conectando en estrella al arrancar y cambiando a delta para operación.","e_en":"A star-delta starter reduces starting current to 1/3 (33%) of LRA by connecting in star at startup and switching to delta for operation.","a":"Un arrancador estrella-delta reduce la corriente de arranque a 1/3 (33%) del LRA conectando en estrella al arrancar y cambiando a delta para operación.","a_en":"A star-delta starter reduces starting current to 1/3 (33%) of LRA by connecting in star at startup and switching to delta for operation."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al medir armónicos en un panel eléctrico con un analizador de potencia, un THD (Total Harmonic Distortion) de 12% indica:","q_en":"When measuring harmonics on an electrical panel with a power analyzer, a THD (Total Harmonic Distortion) of 12% indicates:","o":["Nivel normal aceptable","Nivel elevado que puede causar sobrecalentamiento de transformadores y cables","Nivel crítico, apagar inmediatamente","Solo afecta la iluminación"],"o_en":["Normal acceptable level","Elevated level that can cause overheating of transformers and cables","Critical level, shut down immediately","Only affects lighting"],"c":1,"e":"IEEE 519 recomienda THD <5% para sistemas generales. 12% es elevado y puede causar sobrecalentamiento en transformadores, cables neutros y motores.","e_en":"IEEE 519 recommends THD <5% for general systems. 12% is elevated and can cause overheating in transformers, neutral wires and motors.","a":"IEEE 519 recomienda THD <5% para sistemas generales. 12% es elevado y puede causar sobrecalentamiento en transformadores, cables neutros y motores.","a_en":"IEEE 519 recommends THD <5% for general systems. 12% is elevated and can cause overheating in transformers, neutral wires and motors."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un conductor neutro en un sistema trifásico con cargas no lineales (VFDs, iluminación LED) puede llevar corriente mayor que los conductores de fase porque:","q_en":"A neutral conductor in a three-phase system with non-linear loads (VFDs, LED lighting) can carry more current than phase conductors because:","o":["Error de diseño del sistema","Los armónicos de tercer orden (y múltiplos de 3) se suman en el neutro en lugar de cancelarse","El neutro siempre lleva más corriente","Solo ocurre con sobrecarga"],"o_en":["System design error","Third-order harmonics (and multiples of 3) add up in neutral instead of canceling","Neutral always carries more current","Only happens with overload"],"c":1,"e":"En sistemas balanceados las corrientes del neutro se cancelan. Pero los armónicos de 3er orden (triplen harmonics) se SUMAN en el neutro, pudiendo exceder la corriente de fase.","e_en":"In balanced systems neutral currents cancel. But 3rd-order harmonics (triplen harmonics) ADD UP in neutral, potentially exceeding phase current.","a":"En sistemas balanceados las corrientes del neutro se cancelan. Pero los armónicos de 3er orden (triplen harmonics) se SUMAN en el neutro, pudiendo exceder la corriente de fase.","a_en":"In balanced systems neutral currents cancel. But 3rd-order harmonics (triplen harmonics) ADD UP in neutral, potentially exceeding phase current."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema split de A/C de 5 toneladas necesita un desconectador con capacidad mínima de ampacidad. Si el MCA es 38A, el desconectador debe ser de al menos:","q_en":"A 5-ton split A/C system needs a disconnect with minimum ampacity. If MCA is 38A, the disconnect should be at least:","o":["30A","60A","40A","50A"],"o_en":["30A","60A","40A","50A"],"c":1,"e":"El desconectador debe ser igual o mayor al MCA. Con 38A MCA, el próximo tamaño estándar disponible es 60A.","e_en":"The disconnect must be equal to or greater than MCA. With 38A MCA, the next standard available size is 60A.","a":"El desconectador debe ser igual o mayor al MCA. Con 38A MCA, el próximo tamaño estándar disponible es 60A.","a_en":"The disconnect must be equal to or greater than MCA. With 38A MCA, the next standard available size is 60A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"¿Cuándo se debe usar un contactor con categoría AC-3 vs AC-1?","q_en":"When should you use an AC-3 rated contactor vs AC-1?","o":["AC-3 es para iluminación, AC-1 es para motores","AC-3 es para motores de inducción (arranque/parada frecuente); AC-1 es para cargas resistivas","Son la misma categoría con diferente nombre","AC-1 es para cargas más grandes"],"o_en":["AC-3 is for lighting, AC-1 is for motors","AC-3 is for induction motors (frequent start/stop); AC-1 is for resistive loads","Same category with different name","AC-1 is for larger loads"],"c":1,"e":"AC-3 está diseñado para el estrés de arrancar motores de inducción (alto LRA). AC-1 es para cargas resistivas/ligeramente inductivas sin picos de arranque.","e_en":"AC-3 is designed for the stress of starting induction motors (high LRA). AC-1 is for resistive/slightly inductive loads without startup spikes.","a":"AC-3 está diseñado para el estrés de arrancar motores de inducción (alto LRA). AC-1 es para cargas resistivas/ligeramente inductivas sin picos de arranque.","a_en":"AC-3 is designed for the stress of starting induction motors (high LRA). AC-1 is for resistive/slightly inductive loads without startup spikes."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sensor de humedad capacitivo mide humedad relativa basándose en:","q_en":"A capacitive humidity sensor measures relative humidity based on:","o":["Cambio de resistencia con la humedad","Cambio de capacitancia de un dieléctrico higroscópico con la humedad","Medición de punto de rocío directa","Absorción de luz infrarroja"],"o_en":["Resistance change with humidity","Capacitance change of a hygroscopic dielectric with humidity","Direct dew point measurement","Infrared light absorption"],"c":1,"e":"El sensor capacitivo tiene un dieléctrico que absorbe humedad. A mayor humedad, cambia la capacitancia, que el circuito convierte en señal proporcional.","e_en":"The capacitive sensor has a dielectric that absorbs moisture. More humidity changes capacitance, which the circuit converts to proportional signal.","a":"El sensor capacitivo tiene un dieléctrico que absorbe humedad. A mayor humedad, cambia la capacitancia, que el circuito convierte en señal proporcional.","a_en":"The capacitive sensor has a dielectric that absorbs moisture. More humidity changes capacitance, which the circuit converts to proportional signal."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un relé de sobrecarga electrónico (electronic overload relay) tiene ventaja sobre el bimetálico porque:","q_en":"An electronic overload relay has an advantage over bimetallic because:","o":["Es más barato","Ofrece ajuste preciso, protección contra falla de fase, y no se ve afectado por temperatura ambiente","Es más simple de instalar","Tiene reseteo más rápido"],"o_en":["It's cheaper","Offers precise adjustment, phase failure protection, and isn't affected by ambient temperature","Easier to install","Faster reset"],"c":1,"e":"Los overload electrónicos son más precisos, compensan temperatura ambiente, detectan falla de fase, y permiten ajuste fino del punto de disparo.","e_en":"Electronic overloads are more precise, compensate for ambient temperature, detect phase failure, and allow fine adjustment of trip point.","a":"Los overload electrónicos son más precisos, compensan temperatura ambiente, detectan falla de fase, y permiten ajuste fino del punto de disparo.","a_en":"Electronic overloads are more precise, compensate for ambient temperature, detect phase failure, and allow fine adjustment of trip point."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al medir corriente con un transformador de corriente (CT) de 200:5, si el amperímetro lee 3.5A, ¿cuál es la corriente real del conductor?","q_en":"When measuring current with a 200:5 current transformer (CT), if the ammeter reads 3.5A, what is the actual conductor current?","o":["100A","140A","175A","120A"],"o_en":["100A","140A","175A","120A"],"c":1,"e":"Relación CT 200:5 = 40:1. Corriente real = lectura × relación = 3.5 × 40 = 140A.","e_en":"CT ratio 200:5 = 40:1. Actual current = reading × ratio = 3.5 × 40 = 140A.","a":"Relación CT 200:5 = 40:1. Corriente real = lectura × relación = 3.5 × 40 = 140A.","a_en":"CT ratio 200:5 = 40:1. Actual current = reading × ratio = 3.5 × 40 = 140A."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"NUNCA debes abrir el circuito secundario de un CT (transformador de corriente) mientras hay corriente en el primario porque:","q_en":"You should NEVER open the secondary circuit of a CT (current transformer) while there's current in the primary because:","o":["El CT se desmagnetiza permanentemente","Se genera voltaje peligrosamente alto en el secundario que puede causar electrocución o daño al CT","La lectura se vuelve incorrecta","El primario se sobrecarga"],"o_en":["CT permanently demagnetizes","Dangerously high voltage is generated on secondary that can cause electrocution or CT damage","Reading becomes incorrect","Primary overloads"],"c":1,"e":"Un CT abierto bajo carga genera voltajes de cientos o miles de voltios en el secundario, peligroso para personas y destruye el aislamiento del CT.","e_en":"An open CT under load generates hundreds or thousands of volts on secondary, dangerous to personnel and destroys CT insulation.","a":"Un CT abierto bajo carga genera voltajes de cientos o miles de voltios en el secundario, peligroso para personas y destruye el aislamiento del CT.","a_en":"An open CT under load generates hundreds or thousands of volts on secondary, dangerous to personnel and destroys CT insulation."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor de compresor inverter tiene 3 cables del IPM al motor. Al medir resistencia entre cualquier par de cables, debes obtener:","q_en":"An inverter compressor motor has 3 wires from IPM to motor. When measuring resistance between any pair of wires, you should get:","o":["Valores diferentes en cada par","Valores iguales o muy similares en los tres pares","Un par más alto y dos iguales","OL en todos los pares"],"o_en":["Different values in each pair","Equal or very similar values in all three pairs","One pair higher and two equal","OL in all pairs"],"c":1,"e":"Un motor trifásico de inverter tiene tres devanados iguales. La resistencia entre cualquier par debe ser similar. Diferencia indica problema.","e_en":"An inverter three-phase motor has three equal windings. Resistance between any pair should be similar. Difference indicates a problem.","a":"Un motor trifásico de inverter tiene tres devanados iguales. La resistencia entre cualquier par debe ser similar. Diferencia indica problema.","a_en":"An inverter three-phase motor has three equal windings. Resistance between any pair should be similar. Difference indicates a problem."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"El dip switch en un board de control de un air handler configura típicamente:","q_en":"The dip switch on an air handler control board typically configures:","o":["La dirección IP del equipo","Velocidad del ventilador, tipo de sistema, retardo de tiempo y opciones de operación","Solo el voltaje de operación","La contraseña del termostato"],"o_en":["Equipment IP address","Fan speed, system type, time delays and operating options","Only operating voltage","Thermostat password"],"c":1,"e":"Los dip switches configuran: velocidad del ventilador por modo, tipo de calefacción, retardo del ventilador on/off, y opciones específicas del modelo.","e_en":"Dip switches configure: fan speed per mode, heat type, fan on/off delay, and model-specific options.","a":"Los dip switches configuran: velocidad del ventilador por modo, tipo de calefacción, retardo del ventilador on/off, y opciones específicas del modelo.","a_en":"Dip switches configure: fan speed per mode, heat type, fan on/off delay, and model-specific options."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un LED de diagnóstico en un board de control parpadea 3 veces, pausa, 3 veces. Esto indica un código de error:","q_en":"A diagnostic LED on a control board blinks 3 times, pause, 3 times. This indicates error code:","o":["Código 6","Código 33","Código 3","Código 9"],"o_en":["Code 6","Code 33","Code 3","Code 9"],"c":1,"e":"Los códigos de parpadeo LED típicamente se leen como secuencias separadas por pausas. 3 parpadeos + pausa + 3 parpadeos = código 33.","e_en":"LED blink codes are typically read as sequences separated by pauses. 3 blinks + pause + 3 blinks = code 33.","a":"Los códigos de parpadeo LED típicamente se leen como secuencias separadas por pausas. 3 parpadeos + pausa + 3 parpadeos = código 33.","a_en":"LED blink codes are typically read as sequences separated by pauses. 3 blinks + pause + 3 blinks = code 33."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al reemplazar un board de control, ¿cuál es el paso MÁS IMPORTANTE antes de energizar?","q_en":"When replacing a control board, what is the MOST IMPORTANT step before energizing?","o":["Verificar la versión del firmware","Verificar que todos los cables estén conectados correctamente y que los dip switches coincidan con la configuración original","Limpiar el contacto de los conectores","Probar el transformador primero"],"o_en":["Verify firmware version","Verify all wires are correctly connected and dip switches match original configuration","Clean connector contacts","Test transformer first"],"c":1,"e":"Un cable mal conectado puede destruir el nuevo board. Verifica CADA conexión contra el diagrama y configura los dip switches igual al board original.","e_en":"A miswired connection can destroy the new board. Verify EVERY connection against diagram and set dip switches same as original board.","a":"Un cable mal conectado puede destruir el nuevo board. Verifica CADA conexión contra el diagrama y configura los dip switches igual al board original.","a_en":"A miswired connection can destroy the new board. Verify EVERY connection against diagram and set dip switches same as original board."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control BMS tiene un gateway BACnet-to-Modbus. La función del gateway es:","q_en":"A BMS control system has a BACnet-to-Modbus gateway. The gateway's function is:","o":["Aumentar la velocidad de comunicación","Traducir/convertir protocolos para que dispositivos BACnet y Modbus se comuniquen entre sí","Almacenar datos de tendencia","Amplificar la señal del bus"],"o_en":["Increase communication speed","Translate/convert protocols so BACnet and Modbus devices can communicate with each other","Store trend data","Amplify bus signal"],"c":1,"e":"El gateway traduce entre los dos protocolos. Dispositivos BACnet y Modbus hablan lenguajes diferentes; el gateway actúa como intérprete.","e_en":"The gateway translates between the two protocols. BACnet and Modbus devices speak different languages; the gateway acts as interpreter.","a":"El gateway traduce entre los dos protocolos. Dispositivos BACnet y Modbus hablan lenguajes diferentes; el gateway actúa como intérprete.","a_en":"The gateway translates between the two protocols. BACnet and Modbus devices speak different languages; the gateway acts as interpreter."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un variador de frecuencia muestra código de falla 'OC3' (overcurrent during deceleration). La causa probable es:","q_en":"A VFD shows fault code 'OC3' (overcurrent during deceleration). The probable cause is:","o":["Motor subdimensionado","Tiempo de deceleración demasiado corto para la inercia de la carga","Cable del motor demasiado largo","Voltaje de bus bajo"],"o_en":["Undersized motor","Deceleration time too short for load inertia","Motor cable too long","Low bus voltage"],"c":1,"e":"OC3 durante deceleración indica que la carga tiene mucha inercia y el VFD intenta frenar demasiado rápido. Aumenta el tiempo de deceleración.","e_en":"OC3 during deceleration indicates the load has high inertia and VFD tries to brake too quickly. Increase deceleration time.","a":"OC3 durante deceleración indica que la carga tiene mucha inercia y el VFD intenta frenar demasiado rápido. Aumenta el tiempo de deceleración.","a_en":"OC3 during deceleration indicates the load has high inertia and VFD tries to brake too quickly. Increase deceleration time."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un resistor de frenado (braking resistor) en un VFD se usa cuando:","q_en":"A braking resistor on a VFD is used when:","o":["El motor necesita más torque al arrancar","La carga tiene alta inercia y genera energía de vuelta al VFD durante deceleración","El VFD necesita más potencia de entrada","El motor opera a baja velocidad"],"o_en":["Motor needs more starting torque","Load has high inertia and generates energy back to VFD during deceleration","VFD needs more input power","Motor operates at low speed"],"c":1,"e":"Cuando la carga tiene alta inercia, al frenar genera energía regenerativa. El resistor de frenado disipa esa energía como calor para proteger el bus DC del VFD.","e_en":"When load has high inertia, braking generates regenerative energy. The braking resistor dissipates that energy as heat to protect the VFD DC bus.","a":"Cuando la carga tiene alta inercia, al frenar genera energía regenerativa. El resistor de frenado disipa esa energía como calor para proteger el bus DC del VFD.","a_en":"When load has high inertia, braking generates regenerative energy. The braking resistor dissipates that energy as heat to protect the VFD DC bus."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un condensador trifásico de A/C tiene la fase A a 225V, fase B a 235V, y fase C a 245V. ¿Cuál es el voltaje promedio y el porcentaje de desbalance?","q_en":"A three-phase A/C condenser has phase A at 225V, phase B at 235V, and phase C at 245V. What is the average voltage and imbalance percentage?","o":["230V promedio, 4.3% desbalance","235V promedio, 4.26% desbalance","235V promedio, 2.8% desbalance","230V promedio, 3.5% desbalance"],"o_en":["230V average, 4.3% imbalance","235V average, 4.26% imbalance","235V average, 2.8% imbalance","230V average, 3.5% imbalance"],"c":1,"e":"Promedio = (225+235+245)/3 = 235V. Mayor desviación = 245-235 = 10V. Desbalance = 10/235 × 100 = 4.26%. Excede el 2% máximo.","e_en":"Average = (225+235+245)/3 = 235V. Greatest deviation = 245-235 = 10V. Imbalance = 10/235 × 100 = 4.26%. Exceeds 2% maximum.","a":"Promedio = (225+235+245)/3 = 235V. Mayor desviación = 245-235 = 10V. Desbalance = 10/235 × 100 = 4.26%. Excede el 2% máximo.","a_en":"Average = (225+235+245)/3 = 235V. Greatest deviation = 245-235 = 10V. Imbalance = 10/235 × 100 = 4.26%. Exceeds 2% maximum."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La corriente en un cable neutro de un circuito monofásico 120/240V con carga balanceada es:","q_en":"Current in a neutral wire of a single-phase 120/240V circuit with balanced load is:","o":["Igual a la corriente de las fases","Cero o cerca de cero","El doble de la corriente de fase","La mitad de la corriente de fase"],"o_en":["Equal to phase current","Zero or near zero","Double the phase current","Half the phase current"],"c":1,"e":"Con carga perfectamente balanceada en 120/240V, las corrientes se cancelan en el neutro. En la práctica hay un pequeño desbalance.","e_en":"With perfectly balanced load on 120/240V, currents cancel in the neutral. In practice there's a small imbalance.","a":"Con carga perfectamente balanceada en 120/240V, las corrientes se cancelan en el neutro. En la práctica hay un pequeño desbalance.","a_en":"With perfectly balanced load on 120/240V, currents cancel in the neutral. In practice there's a small imbalance."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un dispositivo TVSS (Transient Voltage Surge Suppressor) para proteger un board de control HVAC se instala:","q_en":"A TVSS (Transient Voltage Surge Suppressor) device to protect an HVAC control board is installed:","o":["En serie con la carga","En paralelo con la carga, lo más cerca posible del equipo protegido","Antes del breaker principal","Después del transformador de control"],"o_en":["In series with the load","In parallel with the load, as close as possible to the protected equipment","Before the main breaker","After the control transformer"],"c":1,"e":"Los supresores de transientes se instalan en PARALELO y lo más cerca posible del equipo para desviar los picos de voltaje a tierra.","e_en":"Surge suppressors are installed in PARALLEL and as close as possible to equipment to divert voltage spikes to ground.","a":"Los supresores de transientes se instalan en PARALELO y lo más cerca posible del equipo para desviar los picos de voltaje a tierra.","a_en":"Surge suppressors are installed in PARALLEL and as close as possible to equipment to divert voltage spikes to ground."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Al instalar un condensador de A/C, el whip (chicote eléctrico) desde el desconectador al equipo no debe exceder:","q_en":"When installing an A/C condenser, the whip (electrical whip) from disconnect to equipment should not exceed:","o":["3 pies","6 pies","10 pies","12 pies"],"o_en":["3 feet","6 feet","10 feet","12 feet"],"c":1,"e":"El whip flexible (conducto flexible) desde el desconectador al equipo no debe exceder 6 pies según la práctica estándar NEC.","e_en":"The flexible whip (flexible conduit) from disconnect to equipment should not exceed 6 feet per standard NEC practice.","a":"El whip flexible (conducto flexible) desde el desconectador al equipo no debe exceder 6 pies según la práctica estándar NEC.","a_en":"The flexible whip (flexible conduit) from disconnect to equipment should not exceed 6 feet per standard NEC practice."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un motor de ventilador de evaporador tiene 4 velocidades. En el board de control, la velocidad del ventilador en modo enfriamiento está en 'MED-HI' pero el flujo de aire es bajo. ¿Qué verificas?","q_en":"An evaporator fan motor has 4 speeds. On the control board, fan speed in cooling mode is set to 'MED-HI' but airflow is low. What do you check?","o":["Cambiar a velocidad HIGH en el board","Verificar filtro de aire, ductos, y que el cable del motor esté conectado a la velocidad correcta (no cruzado)","Reemplazar el motor por uno más potente","Verificar el capacitor del compresor"],"o_en":["Change to HIGH speed on board","Check air filter, ductwork, and that motor wire is connected to correct speed (not crossed)","Replace motor with more powerful one","Check compressor capacitor"],"c":1,"e":"Primero verifica que el cable de velocidad del motor coincida con la selección del board. Cables cruzados o filtro sucio causan bajo flujo.","e_en":"First verify motor speed wire matches board selection. Crossed wires or dirty filter cause low airflow.","a":"Primero verifica que el cable de velocidad del motor coincida con la selección del board. Cables cruzados o filtro sucio causan bajo flujo.","a_en":"First verify motor speed wire matches board selection. Crossed wires or dirty filter cause low airflow."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de control inteligente (smart) pierde comunicación con los sensores remotos durante una tormenta. Después de la tormenta todo funciona menos un sensor. La causa probable es:","q_en":"A smart control system loses communication with remote sensors during a storm. After the storm everything works except one sensor. Probable cause:","o":["Falla del controlador principal","El sensor o su módulo de comunicación fue dañado por un pico de voltaje inducido por rayo","Error de software que se corrige reiniciando","Interferencia electromagnética residual"],"o_en":["Main controller failure","Sensor or its communication module was damaged by lightning-induced voltage spike","Software error corrected by restarting","Residual electromagnetic interference"],"c":1,"e":"Un solo sensor afectado después de una tormenta indica daño por pico de voltaje inducido en el cable de ese sensor. Revisa y reemplaza el sensor/módulo.","e_en":"A single sensor affected after a storm indicates damage from voltage spike induced in that sensor's cable. Check and replace sensor/module.","a":"Un solo sensor afectado después de una tormenta indica daño por pico de voltaje inducido en el cable de ese sensor. Revisa y reemplaza el sensor/módulo.","a_en":"A single sensor affected after a storm indicates damage from voltage spike induced in that sensor's cable. Check and replace sensor/module."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"La impedancia característica de un cable RS-485 para BACnet MS/TP es:","q_en":"The characteristic impedance of RS-485 cable for BACnet MS/TP is:","o":["50 Ω","120 Ω","75 Ω","100 Ω"],"o_en":["50 Ω","120 Ω","75 Ω","100 Ω"],"c":1,"e":"RS-485 usa cable con impedancia característica de 120Ω. Por eso las resistencias de terminación son de 120Ω para igualar la impedancia.","e_en":"RS-485 uses cable with 120Ω characteristic impedance. That's why termination resistors are 120Ω to match impedance.","a":"RS-485 usa cable con impedancia característica de 120Ω. Por eso las resistencias de terminación son de 120Ω para igualar la impedancia.","a_en":"RS-485 uses cable with 120Ω characteristic impedance. That's why termination resistors are 120Ω to match impedance."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema trifásico tiene rotación de fases ABC. Si intercambias las fases A y B, la nueva rotación es:","q_en":"A three-phase system has ABC phase rotation. If you swap phases A and B, the new rotation is:","o":["ABC (sin cambio)","BAC (rotación inversa)","ACB (rotación inversa)","CBA"],"o_en":["ABC (no change)","BAC (reverse rotation)","ACB (reverse rotation)","CBA"],"c":1,"e":"Al intercambiar A y B: donde estaba A ahora está B y viceversa. La secuencia se convierte en BAC, que es rotación inversa.","e_en":"Swapping A and B: where A was, B now is and vice versa. Sequence becomes BAC, which is reverse rotation.","a":"Al intercambiar A y B: donde estaba A ahora está B y viceversa. La secuencia se convierte en BAC, que es rotación inversa.","a_en":"Swapping A and B: where A was, B now is and vice versa. Sequence becomes BAC, which is reverse rotation."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un medidor de secuencia de fases (phase rotation meter) indica rotación incorrecta en un chiller nuevo. Antes de cambiar cables del alimentador, ¿qué debes verificar?","q_en":"A phase rotation meter indicates incorrect rotation on a new chiller. Before changing feeder cables, what should you verify?","o":["Nada, cambia los cables inmediatamente","Verificar con el fabricante cuál es la rotación correcta requerida y confirmar con el medidor en el desconectador","Reemplazar el medidor de fases","Verificar el voltaje primero"],"o_en":["Nothing, change cables immediately","Verify with manufacturer the correct required rotation and confirm with meter at the disconnect","Replace the phase meter","Check voltage first"],"c":1,"e":"Antes de cambiar cables, confirma la rotación requerida con el fabricante y mide en el punto correcto (desconectador del equipo, no el panel principal).","e_en":"Before changing cables, confirm required rotation with manufacturer and measure at correct point (equipment disconnect, not main panel).","a":"Antes de cambiar cables, confirma la rotación requerida con el fabricante y mide en el punto correcto (desconectador del equipo, no el panel principal).","a_en":"Before changing cables, confirm required rotation with manufacturer and measure at correct point (equipment disconnect, not main panel)."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema rooftop tiene un economizer con entalpía. El sensor de entalpía mide:","q_en":"A rooftop system has an enthalpy economizer. The enthalpy sensor measures:","o":["Solo temperatura del aire","Temperatura y humedad del aire para calcular contenido total de calor","Solo humedad relativa","Velocidad del aire y temperatura"],"o_en":["Only air temperature","Air temperature and humidity to calculate total heat content","Only relative humidity","Air velocity and temperature"],"c":1,"e":"Un sensor de entalpía mide temperatura y humedad para determinar el contenido total de calor (BTU/lb) del aire y decidir si el aire exterior es más favorable.","e_en":"An enthalpy sensor measures temperature and humidity to determine total heat content (BTU/lb) of air and decide if outdoor air is more favorable.","a":"Un sensor de entalpía mide temperatura y humedad para determinar el contenido total de calor (BTU/lb) del aire y decidir si el aire exterior es más favorable.","a_en":"An enthalpy sensor measures temperature and humidity to determine total heat content (BTU/lb) of air and decide if outdoor air is more favorable."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un circuito de control modular 24V alimenta 8 dispositivos. Si el cable total tiene 200 pies de longitud ida y vuelta en AWG 18, ¿cuál es la caída de voltaje aproximada a 2A?","q_en":"A modular 24V control circuit powers 8 devices. If total wire length is 200 feet round trip in AWG 18, what is the approximate voltage drop at 2A?","o":["0.5V","2.6V","1.2V","3.8V"],"o_en":["0.5V","2.6V","1.2V","3.8V"],"c":1,"e":"AWG 18: ~6.5Ω por 1000 pies. Para 200 pies: 200/1000 × 6.5 = 1.3Ω. Caída = I × R = 2 × 1.3 = 2.6V. Es >10% de 24V, necesita cable más grueso.","e_en":"AWG 18: ~6.5Ω per 1000 feet. For 200 feet: 200/1000 × 6.5 = 1.3Ω. Drop = I × R = 2 × 1.3 = 2.6V. >10% of 24V, needs thicker wire.","a":"AWG 18: ~6.5Ω por 1000 pies. Para 200 pies: 200/1000 × 6.5 = 1.3Ω. Caída = I × R = 2 × 1.3 = 2.6V. Es >10% de 24V, necesita cable más grueso.","a_en":"AWG 18: ~6.5Ω per 1000 feet. For 200 feet: 200/1000 × 6.5 = 1.3Ω. Drop = I × R = 2 × 1.3 = 2.6V. >10% of 24V, needs thicker wire."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"Un sistema de refrigeración comercial con rack de compresores tiene un controlador que maneja 'pump-down'. ¿Qué hace el pump-down?","q_en":"A commercial refrigeration system with compressor rack has a controller that manages 'pump-down'. What does pump-down do?","o":["Bombea aceite de regreso al compresor","Cierra la válvula de líquido y permite al compresor bombear el refrigerante del evaporador al condensador/recibidor antes de apagarse","Reduce la presión de descarga","Bombea refrigerante líquido al evaporador"],"o_en":["Pumps oil back to compressor","Closes liquid valve and allows compressor to pump refrigerant from evaporator to condenser/receiver before shutting off","Reduces discharge pressure","Pumps liquid refrigerant to evaporator"],"c":1,"e":"Pump-down cierra la válvula solenoide de líquido y el compresor evacua el refrigerante del evaporador al condensador antes de apagarse, previniendo migración.","e_en":"Pump-down closes the liquid solenoid valve and compressor evacuates refrigerant from evaporator to condenser before shutting off, preventing migration.","a":"Pump-down cierra la válvula solenoide de líquido y el compresor evacua el refrigerante del evaporador al condensador antes de apagarse, previniendo migración.","a_en":"Pump-down closes the liquid solenoid valve and compressor evacuates refrigerant from evaporator to condenser before shutting off, preventing migration."},{"cat":"Estudio de Electricidad","cat_en":"Electricity Study","q":"En un sistema con múltiples compresores en paralelo (rack), el controlador de capacidad activa los compresores escalonadamente. Si la demanda baja, ¿cuál compresor se apaga primero?","q_en":"In a system with multiple parallel compressors (rack), the capacity controller stages compressors on sequentially. If demand drops, which compressor shuts off first?","o":["El más grande","El último que se encendió (LIFO - Last In First Out)","El más pequeño","Todos al mismo tiempo"],"o_en":["The largest one","The last one turned on (LIFO - Last In First Out)","The smallest one","All at the same time"],"c":1,"e":"La lógica LIFO apaga el último compresor en encender primero. Esto equaliza las horas de operación y reduce ciclos en compresores individuales.","e_en":"LIFO logic shuts off the last compressor turned on first. This equalizes run hours and reduces cycling on individual compressors.","a":"La lógica LIFO apaga el último compresor en encender primero. Esto equaliza las horas de operación y reduce ciclos en compresores individuales.","a_en":"LIFO logic shuts off the last compressor turned on first. This equalizes run hours and reduces cycling on individual compressors."}];